{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SRSqAAq3cmdJVaa42x313W","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Docker Compose configuration for OfficeAgent\n     2→# Focuses on containerized OfficeAgent API service\n     3→# Token Server and Test Client run natively (see scripts/start.mjs)\n     4→#\n     5→# Usage:\n     6→#   Single container:  docker compose up -d\n     7→#   Scale to 3:        docker compose up -d --scale officeagent=3\n     8→#   Scale to 5:        docker compose up -d --scale officeagent=5\n     9→#   With load balancer: docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.loadbalancer.yml up -d --scale officeagent=3\n    10→#\n    11→# Lumina image (alternative):\n    12→#   docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.lumina.yml up -d\n    13→#\n    14→# Prerequisites:\n    15→#   - Token Server running on host (yarn start:token or scripts/start.mjs)\n    16→#   - Python eval framework will auto-discover all running containers\n    17→\n    18→services:\n    19→  # Main OfficeAgent API Service\n    20→  # Scales dynamically with automatic port assignment\n    21→  officeagent:\n    22→    image: officeagent:devlatest\n    23→    build:\n    24→      context: .\n    25→      dockerfile: docker/Dockerfile\n    26→      secrets:\n    27→        - pip_index_url\n    28→        - npm_secret\n    29→        - npm_home_secret\n    30→      args:\n    31→        - EXT_BUILD_SPEC=dev\n    32→    environment:\n    33→      # Development configuration\n    34→      OfficePy__Deployment__LocalhostOfficeAgentDevelopment: \"True\"\n    35→      OfficePy__ProcessTracer__IsDisabled: \"True\"\n    36→      OfficePy__HealthCheckDisabled: \"False\"\n    37→      # Dynamic data paths\n    38→      OfficePy__DataUploadPath: \"/home/jovyan/data_upload\"\n    39→      OfficePy__FileManager__FolderPath: \"/home/jovyan/file_upload\"\n    40→      # Agent configuration (defaults to create-agent if not set)\n    41→      OAGENT_AGENTID: ${OAGENT_AGENTID:-create-agent}\n    42→      # Flight flags for container-side feature gates\n    43→      OAGENT_FLIGHTS: ${OAGENT_FLIGHTS:-}\n    44→      # GitHub Copilot SDK authentication (auto-downloads CLI on first use)\n    45→      GITHUB_TOKEN: ${GITHUB_TOKEN:-}\n    46→    env_file:\n    47→      - ./docker/copilot.env\n    48→    ports:\n    49→      # Docker automatically assigns host ports\n    50→      # Query assigned ports: docker compose port officeagent 6010\n    51→      - \"6010\"  # External API port (e.g., 6010, 49153, 49154...)\n    52→      - \"6011\"  # Internal API port\n    53→      - \"6020\"  # Node.js debug port\n    54→      - \"7010\"  # Grounding agent internal HTTP port\n    55→    healthcheck:\n    56→      test: [\"CMD\", \"curl\", \"-f\", \"http://localhost:6010/health\"]\n    57→      interval: 10s\n    58→      timeout: 5s\n    59→      retries: 5\n    60→      start_period: 30s\n    61→    networks:\n    62→      - officeagent-net\n    63→    restart: unless-stopped\n    64→    # Resource limits (optional, adjust as needed)\n    65→    # deploy:\n    66→    #   resources:\n    67→    #     limits:\n    68→    #       cpus: '2'\n    69→    #       memory: 4G\n    70→    #     reservations:\n    71→    #       cpus: '1'\n    72→    #       memory: 2G\n    73→\n    74→networks:\n    75→  officeagent-net:\n    76→    driver: bridge\n    77→    name: officeagent-network\n    78→\n    79→# Docker secrets for authentication\n    80→secrets:\n    81→  pip_index_url:\n    82→    file: ./docker/public-pip-index-url.txt\n    83→  npm_secret:\n    84→    file: ./docker/.npmrc\n    85→  npm_home_secret:\n    86→    file: ${HOME:-${USERPROFILE}}/.npmrc\n    87→\n    88→# Optional: Persistent volumes\n    89→# volumes:\n    90→#   officeagent-data:\n    91→#     driver: local\n    92→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JgzknBttobEMZ4qK1jH68n","session_id":"059c34c4-4758-4e2f-87ba-9357713e7c91","uuid":"eee64c7e-8471-42c8-92b3-4dbca228f9e8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VsqB9oFUHhw9NTBzRUM1PQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Eval Framework - Quick Reference\n     2→\n     3→> Full documentation: [README.md](./README.md)\n     4→\n     5→## Running Evals\n     6→\n     7→```powershell\n     8→# List all available aliases\n     9→oagent eval alias\n    10→\n    11→# Quick single-test smoke check\n    12→oagent eval ppt.example\n    13→\n    14→# Full suites by document type\n    15→oagent eval ppt.ungrounded          # PPT without grounding\n    16→oagent eval ppt.groundingeval       # PPT with grounding\n    17→oagent eval word.groundingeval      # Word with grounding\n    18→oagent eval excel.ungrounded        # Excel generation\n    19→oagent eval excel.pairwise          # Excel pairwise comparison\n    20→oagent eval excel.locale            # Excel locale/language tests\n    21→\n    22→# Limit to first N test cases\n    23→oagent eval ppt.groundingeval -n 3\n    24→\n    25→# Custom batch + config\n    26→oagent eval run --batch ./eval/datasets/my_tests.json --config ./eval/configs/my_config.json\n    27→\n    28→# Single prompt submission\n    29→oagent eval submit --prompt \"Create a sales report\" --type pptx\n    30→```\n    31→\n    32→**Prerequisites**: Docker Desktop running, `npm run setup` completed, containers started with `yarn start:compose`.\n    33→\n    34→## Directory Map\n    35→\n    36→```\n    37→eval/\n    38→├── aliases.json              # Alias definitions (name -> batch + config)\n    39→├── README.md                 # Comprehensive documentation\n    40→├── configs/                  # Eval configuration JSON files\n    41→├── datasets/                 # Test datasets (batch JSON files)\n    42→├── src/\n    43→│   ├── cli.py                # CLI entry point (oagent eval)\n    44→│   ├── framework.py          # Main EvalFramework orchestrator\n    45→│   ├── types.py              # EvalRequest, EvalConfig, EvalResult models\n    46→│   ├── evaluators/           # Modular evaluators (see table below)\n    47→│   │   ├── base.py           # Evaluator base class\n    48→│   │   └── *.py              # Individual evaluator implementations\n    49→│   ├── preprocessors/        # Data extraction before evaluation\n    50→│   ├── scrapers/             # Document generation via API\n    51→│   └── utils/                # Shared utilities\n    52→├── prompt_templates/         # LLM evaluation prompts\n    53→├── scripts/\n    54→│   ├── xlsx/perf/            # Excel A/B testing scripts\n    55→│   └── pptx/                 # PPT batch generation & evaluation\n    56→├── experiments/              # Experimental evals\n    57→└── outputs/                  # Generated results (gitignored)\n    58→```\n    59→\n    60→## Output Structure\n    61→\n    62→```\n    63→eval/outputs/<run_name>/\n    64→├── eval_report_<run_name>_<timestamp>.json   # Aggregate report\n    65→└── <test_id>/\n    66→    └── <app_name>/                           # Default: \"officeagent\"\n    67→        ├── doc/                              # Generated document + debug\n    68→        │   ├── *.xlsx / *.pptx / *.docx\n    69→        │   ├── scrape_result.json            # Generation outcome\n    70→        │   └── debug/logs/officeagent.log    # Agent logs\n    71→        └── eval/                             # Evaluation results\n    72→            └── excel_result_run1.json        # Consolidated results\n    73→```\n    74→\n    75→## Evaluators\n    76→\n    77→> **Canonical list**: See `evaluator_map` in `eval/src/framework.py`.\n    78→> Registration: `eval/src/evaluators/__init__.py`.\n    79→\n    80→### Commonly used evaluators\n    81→\n    82→| Config Name | Document Types | Scoring |\n    83→|-------------|---------------|---------|\n    84→| `\"excel\"` | xlsx | 1-5 scale: accuracy, completeness, usefulness, reliability, aesthetics |\n    85→| `\"pairwise\"` | pptx, docx, xlsx | Side-by-side comparison (xlsx uses ExcelComparisonHelper) |\n    86→| `\"societas\"` | pptx, docx | Visual quality (fidelity, aesthetics, consistency, storytelling) |\n    87→| `\"content\"` | pptx, docx | Content quality |\n    88→| `\"rule_based\"` | pptx | Deterministic rules (slide count, bullets) |\n    89→| `\"intent\"` | all | Artifact generation intent detection |\n    90→\n    91→## Creating New Evaluators\n    92→\n    93→1. Create class in `eval/src/evaluators/` extending `Evaluator` base\n    94→2. Implement `_evaluate_impl(requests, responses, run_number)` (required)\n    95→3. Optionally override `summarize_report()` and `validate_requests()`\n    96→4. Register in `eval/src/evaluators/__init__.py`\n    97→5. Add evaluator name to config's `\"evaluators\"` list\n    98→\n    99→## Batch File Format\n   100→\n   101→```json\n   102→{\n   103→  \"run_name\": \"my_eval_run\",\n   104→  \"requests\": [\n   105→    {\n   106→      \"prompt\": \"Create a spreadsheet tracking Q4 sales\",\n   107→      \"document_type\": \"xlsx\",\n   108→      \"metadata\": { \"test_id\": \"excel1\", \"theme\": \"Office\" },\n   109→      \"timeout\": 2700,\n   110→      \"flights\": [\"OfficeAgent.EnableCreateAgentV2:true\"]\n   111→    }\n   112→  ]\n   113→}\n   114→```\n   115→\n   116→Required: `prompt`, `document_type`, `metadata.test_id`.\n   117→\n   118→## Excel Eval Notes\n   119→\n   120→### Evaluation Dimensions (1-5 scale each)\n   121→- **Accuracy**: Query understanding and implementation correctness\n   122→- **Completeness**: Coverage of all query requirements\n   123→- **Usefulness**: Practical value and effectiveness\n   124→- **Reliability**: Technical quality and robustness (formulas, data types)\n   125→- **Aesthetics**: Visual appeal and professional presentation\n   126→\n   127→### Output Analysis\n   128→\n   129→Check `scrape_result.json` for generation outcome:\n   130→- `*.xlsx` in output_path = generated Excel document\n   131→- `presentationConfig.json` = asked clarification questions (turn 2)\n   132→- `chatMessage_resultMessage.txt` = agent returned a chat response instead of a document (note: this file is no longer written to disk by the agent — it exists only as a virtual filename for signaling. The actual agent response is only in WebSocket messages and `officeagent.log` under `Result message:` / `Summarized result message:`)\n   133→\n   134→### Key Log Patterns (officeagent.log)\n   135→\n   136→| Pattern | Meaning |\n   137→|---------|---------|\n   138→| `Result message: [NO_SUMMARIZE]` | Generation subagent result (full content) |\n   139→| `[NO_SUMMARIZE] block detected, skipping summarization` | Summarization correctly skipped |\n   140→| `Summarized result message:` | What user actually sees |\n   141→| `[FetchRetriever] getContent returned: N chars` | Grounding file retrieval |\n   142→\n   143→### Detecting Agent Assumptions/Fabrication\n   144→\n   145→Search Result message in logs for:\n   146→\n   147→| Pattern | Risk |\n   148→|---------|------|\n   149→| `\"sample of X\"` / `\"representative sample\"` | Sampled instead of full dataset |\n   150→| `\"too large for\"` / `\"too many rows\"` | Claimed data too big |\n   151→| `\"no data was provided\"` / `\"data not found\"` | Couldn't access grounded file |\n   152→| `\"generated sample data\"` / `\"synthetic\"` | Fabricated data |\n   153→| `\"Assumption:\"` block | Made assumptions - read carefully |\n   154→\n   155→### Data Mismatch Detection\n   156→\n   157→Check `content.md` in debug workspace for:\n   158→- `\"CRITICAL DATA MISMATCH ALERT\"` or `\"ALERT: Data Mismatch\"`\n   159→- Sheet names that don't match expected content\n   160→\n   161→### Excel Issues Checklist\n   162→\n   163→- [ ] Did all tests generate documents? (check `output_generated_count`)\n   164→- [ ] Any clarification loops? (check `clarification_question_count`)\n   165→- [ ] NO_SUMMARIZE working? (search logs for \"skipping summarization\")\n   166→- [ ] Any sampling/assumptions? (search Result message for patterns above)\n   167→- [ ] Data mismatches? (check content.md for alerts)\n   168→- [ ] Formula accuracy? (eval accuracy score < 3 warrants investigation)\n   169→- [ ] Tip: Add `\"; do not go into turn 2 for clarification\"` to prompts to prevent loops\n   170→\n   171→### Excel Perf Analysis (A/B Testing)\n   172→\n   173→```powershell\n   174→# From eval/scripts/xlsx/perf/\n   175→.\\find-outliers.ps1\n   176→.\\analyze-xlsx-perf.ps1 -Control \"create_01-15\" -Treatment \"create_16-30\"\n   177→```\n   178→\n   179→## Debugging Eval Failures\n   180→\n   181→1. **No containers found**: `docker ps`, then `yarn start:compose`\n   182→2. **Timeout errors**: Increase `\"timeout\"` in batch file or config (default: 1800s)\n   183→3. **Reuse cached results**: `\"reuse_document_files\": true` and `\"reuse_evaluation_files\": true`\n   184→4. **Container logs**: `docker compose logs officeagent`\n   185→5. **Score breakdown**: Check per-test JSON in `eval/outputs/<run>/<test_id>/<app>/eval/`\n   186→\n   187→## Config Defaults\n   188→\n   189→| Setting | Default |\n   190→|---------|---------|\n   191→| `api_port` | 6010 |\n   192→| `timeout` | 1800s |\n   193→| `max_retries` | 0 |\n   194→| `generation_batch_size` | 1 |\n   195→| `evaluation_batch_size` | 1 |\n   196→| `evaluation_model` | `dev-gpt-5-reasoning` |\n   197→| `output_dir` | `./eval/outputs` |\n   198→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JgzknBttobEMZ4qK1jH68n","session_id":"059c34c4-4758-4e2f-87ba-9357713e7c91","uuid":"bb696b27-ea35-48b8-b67f-504c1cf2f63f"}
