{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BxrW8wexLMzwjXNcdzdTaQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Create Agent - Developer Quick Reference\n     2→\n     3→> See [README.md](README.md) for full architecture docs, flight/filter system details, and how to create custom skills/sub-agents.\n     4→\n     5→## What This Agent Does\n     6→\n     7→Autonomous document creation agent powered by Claude. Generates PowerPoint (.pptx), Word (.docx), and Excel (.xlsx) files from natural language requests. Runs as a WebSocket service inside Docker.\n     8→\n     9→## Team-Specific Documentation\n    10→\n    11→Different teams work on different document types. See the relevant guide for your area:\n    12→\n    13→- **[CLAUDE_EXCEL.md](CLAUDE_EXCEL.md)** - Excel team: headless Excel service, Office.js, xlsx pipeline\n    14→- **[CLAUDE_POWERPOINT.md](CLAUDE_POWERPOINT.md)** - PowerPoint team: HTML-to-PPTX conversion, pptx pipeline\n    15→- **[CLAUDE_WORD.md](CLAUDE_WORD.md)** - Word team: JSON-to-OOXML conversion, docx pipeline\n    16→\n    17→## Key Files\n    18→\n    19→| File | Purpose |\n    20→|------|---------|\n    21→| `src/create-agent.ts` | Main agent class. WebSocket routing, Claude orchestration, system prompt building |\n    22→| `src/registry.ts` | Agent config: versions, model settings, skills, sub-agents, flights, filters. **Edit this to add/remove capabilities** |\n    23→| `src/types.ts` | Core types: `AgentType` enum (word/excel/powerpoint), `GeneratedFileInfo`, `DocumentGenerationCallbacks` |\n    24→| `src/constants.ts` | Flight key constants, artifact type constants |\n    25→| `src/hooks/` | Agent-specific Claude hooks: `base-hooks.ts` (shared), `excel-hooks.ts`, `ppt-hooks.ts`, `word-hooks.ts` |\n    26→| `src/services/` | File watcher, WebSocket messenger, Claude logger, perf tracker, query interrupt, chat history, agent state |\n    27→| `src/sidecar/query-classifier/` | Fire-and-forget query classification for telemetry |\n    28→| `src/sandbox/excel-office-js-sandbox.ts` | Sandboxed Office.js execution for Excel |\n    29→\n    30→## Prompt Versions\n    31→\n    32→- **1.0.0** (default) - Enterprise search sub-agents (enterprise-search, analysts, curator), legacy docx-page-subagent\n    33→- **1.1.0** (behind `OfficeAgent.EnableCreateAgent@1.1.0` flight) - New sub-agent pipelines with outline generators, content extractors, Office.js generators. Has `overwrites/` for flight-based prompt replacement\n    34→\n    35→### Prompt Directory Structure (per version)\n    36→\n    37→```\n    38→src/prompts/<version>/\n    39→  system-prompt.md          # EJS template - main system prompt\n    40→  rai.md                    # Responsible AI guidelines\n    41→  agent-capabilities/       # Per-type descriptions (excel.md, word.md, powerpoint.md)\n    42→  intent-detection/         # Request interceptor prompts\n    43→  skills/                   # Skill definitions (see below)\n    44→  subagents/                # Sub-agent definitions (.md with frontmatter)\n    45→  scripts/                  # Runtime scripts deployed to agent workspace\n    46→  overwrites/               # (1.1.0 only) Flight-conditional file replacements\n    47→```\n    48→\n    49→## Skills Overview\n    50→\n    51→Skills live in `src/prompts/<version>/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`.\n    52→\n    53→| Skill | Description |\n    54→|-------|-------------|\n    55→| **xlsx** | Excel creation via Office.js + headless Excel |\n    56→| **pptx** | PowerPoint via HTML-to-PPTX conversion |\n    57→| **docx** | Word document generation |\n    58→| **image-search** | Image search integration |\n    59→| **enterprise-research** | (1.0.0) Multi-step enterprise data workflow |\n    60→| **web-search**, **web-fetch**, **pdf** | Additional capabilities |\n    61→\n    62→## Sub-Agents by Version\n    63→\n    64→**1.0.0**: `pptx-html-creator-validator`, `pptx-outline-validator`, `docx-page-subagent`, `enterprise-search`, `enterprise-*-analyst` (6 types), `enterprise-curator`\n    65→\n    66→**1.1.0**: `xlsx-resource-discovery` -> `xlsx-content-extractor` -> `xlsx-outline-generator` -> `xlsx-office-js-generator` | `pptx-outline-generator` -> `pptx-html-creator-validator` | `docx-outline-generator` -> `docx-section-generator`\n    67→\n    68→## How To: Common Changes\n    69→\n    70→### Add a New Skill\n    71→1. Create `src/prompts/<version>/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` with YAML frontmatter (`name`, `description`)\n    72→2. Add skill name to `skills` array in `src/registry.ts`\n    73→3. Optionally gate behind a flight\n    74→\n    75→### Add a New Sub-Agent\n    76→1. Create `src/prompts/<version>/subagents/<name>.md` with YAML frontmatter\n    77→2. Add to `subagents` array in `src/registry.ts`\n    78→3. Invoke from skills/prompts using Task tool\n    79→\n    80→### Add a New Flight\n    81→1. Add entry to `flights` array in `src/registry.ts`\n    82→2. Specify `flightKey`, optional `applicableVersions`, and `config` overrides\n    83→3. Enable via `.env`: `OAGENT_FLIGHTS=<flightKey>:true`\n    84→\n    85→### Add Agent-Specific Hooks\n    86→1. Create/modify provider in `src/hooks/` (implements `HookProvider` from core)\n    87→2. Register in `CreateAgent` constructor via `hookRegistry.register(AgentType.X, new XHooksProvider())`\n    88→\n    89→## Excel-Specific Notes\n    90→\n    91→- Excel files are created **in the cloud** (SharePoint/OneDrive) via headless Excel service, NOT on local filesystem\n    92→- `ExcelHooksProvider` blocks direct .xlsx file creation via Write/Bash tools\n    93→- Excel headless handlers registered during `initialize()` via `registerExcelHeadlessHandlers()`\n    94→- The `excel-headless` module provides the Excel API\n    95→- Excel download: behind `ExcelDownload` flight\n    96→- **1.1.0 xlsx pipeline (default)**: resource-discovery -> content-extractor -> outline-generator -> office-js-generator\n    97→- **1.1.0 xlsx pipeline v1** (behind `OfficeAgent.CreateAgent.XlsxPipelineV1`): 4-step with separate validator\n    98→- Visual description: behind `OfficeAgent.XlsxVisualDescription` flight\n    99→\n   100→## Dependencies\n   101→\n   102→| Package | What It Provides |\n   103→|---------|-----------------|\n   104→| `@officeagent/core` | BaseAgent, SessionContext, AgentWorkspaceManager, HookRegistry, logging |\n   105→| `@officeagent/chain-of-thought` | Progress indicators sent to client |\n   106→| `@officeagent/excel-headless` | Headless Excel service for cloud .xlsx creation |\n   107→| `@officeagent/grounding` | Parses grounding content from request context |\n   108→| `@officeagent/message-protocol` | Message types, WebSocket protocol |\n   109→| `@officeagent/rai` | Responsible AI filtering |\n   110→\n   111→## Development\n   112→\n   113→```powershell\n   114→yarn build          # Build (gulp)\n   115→oagent gen \"query\"  # Test locally (requires .env setup)\n   116→yarn test           # Unit tests\n   117→```\n   118→\n   119→Required `.env`:\n   120→```\n   121→OAGENT_AGENTID=create-agent\n   122→OAGENT_FLIGHTS=OfficeAgent.EnableEnterpriseSubstrateStrategy:true  # optional\n   123→```\n   124→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VcS2pjCQDmBrQu85ZKAMvr","session_id":"059c34c4-4758-4e2f-87ba-9357713e7c91","uuid":"6c9ad24c-ffe7-466f-8e63-ad6c9e9113b2"}
