{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01A9m1zk1AXYrD5P1QPJBPQp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: office-agent-failure-analysis\n     3→description: Fetches all error data from Augloop Kusto data, analyzes and projects analysis in html\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Skill: OfficeAgentTask Failure Analysis Report\n     7→\n     8→## Description\n     9→Analyze OfficeAgentTask failures from the ODX AugLoop Service Kusto database, cross-reference with Azure DevOps work items, and generate a styled HTML browser report with ACE/ICE error rate projections and ring-level breakdowns.\n    10→\n    11→## When to Use\n    12→- When asked to analyze OfficeAgentTask failures or reliability\n    13→- When asked to generate a failure/error report for Office Agent\n    14→- When asked about ACE (Actionable Customer Errors) or ICE (Including all Customer Errors) rates\n    15→- When asked to cross-reference Kusto failures with ADO bugs\n    16→\n    17→## Data Sources\n    18→- **Kusto Database**: `ODX AugLoop Service`\n    19→- **Table**: `WorkflowOperationEvent`\n    20→- **Filter**: `operationName == \"OfficeAgentTask\"` and `success == 0`\n    21→- **ADO Project**: `OC` (search across all work item types)\n    22→\n    23→## Key Fields in WorkflowOperationEvent\n    24→- `operationName` — filter for `\"OfficeAgentTask\"`\n    25→- `success` — `0` = failure, `1` = success\n    26→- `Tenant` — first part (before `_`) is the ring: `dogfood`, `msit`, `prod`\n    27→- `durationMs` — operation duration in milliseconds\n    28→- `dataFields` — JSON string containing:\n    29→  - `failureReason` — e.g. `TaskFailed`, `WorkflowAborted`, `AgentUnavailableForUser`\n    30→  - `lastStage` — e.g. `Initialization`, `Processing`, `Aborted`, `Failed`\n    31→  - `agentId` — e.g. `PowerPoint`, `Excel`, `Word`\n    32→  - `aborted` — `true`/`false`\n    33→- `clientAppName`, `clientAppPlatform` — client surface info\n    34→\n    35→## Expected (Non-Actionable) Errors\n    36→These are NOT bugs and should be excluded from ACE calculations:\n    37→- **AgentUnavailableForUser** — Tenants that have not enabled Office Agent for their users\n    38→- **WorkflowAborted** — User-initiated cancellations during processing\n    39→- **ConversationExpired** — Normal session timeout behavior\n    40→\n    41→## Report Generation Script\n    42→\n    43→A Python script (`generate_report.py`) in this skill folder generates the styled HTML report from collected data. The agent collects data from Kusto and ADO, writes it to a JSON file, then runs the script.\n    44→\n    45→### Script Location\n    46→```\n    47→.github/skills/office-agent-failure-analysis/generate_report.py\n    48→```\n    49→\n    50→### Script Usage\n    51→```bash\n    52→python generate_report.py <input_json_path> [output_html_path]\n    53→```\n    54→\n    55→### Input JSON Schema\n    56→The agent must create a JSON file with this structure:\n    57→```json\n    58→{\n    59→  \"time_range\": {\n    60→    \"type\": \"duration\",\n    61→    \"duration_days\": 1\n    62→  },\n    63→  \"failures\": [\n    64→    { \"FailureCount\": 30, \"agentId\": \"Excel\", \"failureReason\": \"TaskFailed\", \"ring\": \"prod\" }\n    65→  ],\n    66→  \"ace_ice_by_ring\": [\n    67→    { \"ring\": \"prod\", \"Total\": 8875, \"AllFailures\": 440, \"ActionableFailures\": 120, \"ICE\": 4.96, \"ACE\": 1.35 }\n    68→  ],\n    69→  \"ace_ice_by_agent_ring\": [\n    70→    { \"agentId\": \"Excel\", \"ring\": \"prod\", \"Total\": 2515, \"AllFailures\": 145, \"ActionableFailures\": 65, \"ICE\": 5.77, \"ACE\": 2.58 }\n    71→  ],\n    72→  \"ado_items\": {\n    73→    \"TaskFailed\": [\n    74→      { \"id\": 11152394, \"title\": \"Bug title\", \"state\": \"New\", \"assignedTo\": \"Name\" }\n    75→    ]\n    76→  }\n    77→}\n    78→```\n    79→\n    80→## Time Range Parameters\n    81→\n    82→The agent accepts time range input in two formats:\n    83→\n    84→### Duration in Days\n    85→User specifies a number of days to look back from now.\n    86→- Example: `7d`, `3d`, `30d`\n    87→- KQL filter: `| where TIMESTAMP > ago(7d)`\n    88→- Default: `1d` if no time range is specified\n    89→\n    90→### UTC Time Range\n    91→User specifies explicit start and end timestamps in UTC.\n    92→- Example: `2026-02-01T00:00:00Z` to `2026-02-13T00:00:00Z`\n    93→- KQL filter: `| where TIMESTAMP between (datetime(2026-02-01T00:00:00Z) .. datetime(2026-02-13T00:00:00Z))`\n    94→\n    95→### Interpretation Rules\n    96→1. If the user says \"last 7 days\" or \"7d\" → use `ago(7d)`\n    97→2. If the user gives a date range → use `between (datetime(...) .. datetime(...))`\n    98→3. If no time range is mentioned → default to `ago(1d)`\n    99→4. Pass the resolved time range info in the input JSON `time_range` field (see schema below)\n   100→\n   101→## Step-by-Step Process\n   102→\n   103→### 0. Ask User for Time Range\n   104→Before running any Kusto queries, **prompt the user** to specify the time range for the analysis. Present these options:\n   105→- **Duration in days**: e.g., \"Last 1 day\", \"Last 7 days\", \"Last 30 days\"\n   106→- **UTC time range**: e.g., \"2026-02-01 to 2026-02-13\"\n   107→- **Default**: If the user doesn't specify or says \"default\", use `ago(1d)` (last 24 hours)\n   108→\n   109→Use the `ask_user` tool with choices like:\n   110→```\n   111→\"Last 1 day (default)\", \"Last 3 days\", \"Last 7 days\", \"Last 14 days\", \"Last 30 days\", \"Custom UTC time range\"\n   112→```\n   113→\n   114→If the user selects \"Custom UTC time range\", follow up by asking for the start and end timestamps.\n   115→\n   116→Store the resolved time range to:\n   117→1. Use in all subsequent KQL queries (replace `ago(1d)` with the appropriate filter)\n   118→2. Pass in the `time_range` field of the input JSON for the report generator\n   119→\n   120→### 1. Query Failures from Kusto\n   121→\n   122→#### Using duration (default):\n   123→```kql\n   124→WorkflowOperationEvent\n   125→| where operationName == \"OfficeAgentTask\"\n   126→| where success == 0\n   127→| where TIMESTAMP > ago(1d)\n   128→| extend ring = tostring(split(Tenant, \"_\")[0])\n   129→| extend failureReason = extract(@'\"failureReason\":\"([^\"]+)\"', 1, dataFields)\n   130→| extend lastStage = extract(@'\"lastStage\":\"([^\"]+)\"', 1, dataFields)\n   131→| extend agentId = extract(@'\"agentId\":\"([^\"]+)\"', 1, dataFields)\n   132→| extend aborted = extract(@'\"aborted\":(true|false)', 1, dataFields)\n   133→| summarize FailureCount = count(),\n   134→            AvgDurationMs = avg(durationMs)\n   135→            by failureReason, lastStage, agentId, aborted, clientAppName, clientAppPlatform, ring\n   136→| order by FailureCount desc\n   137→```\n   138→\n   139→#### Using UTC time range:\n   140→```kql\n   141→WorkflowOperationEvent\n   142→| where operationName == \"OfficeAgentTask\"\n   143→| where success == 0\n   144→| where TIMESTAMP between (datetime(2026-02-01T00:00:00Z) .. datetime(2026-02-13T00:00:00Z))\n   145→| extend ring = tostring(split(Tenant, \"_\")[0])\n   146→| extend failureReason = extract(@'\"failureReason\":\"([^\"]+)\"', 1, dataFields)\n   147→| extend lastStage = extract(@'\"lastStage\":\"([^\"]+)\"', 1, dataFields)\n   148→| extend agentId = extract(@'\"agentId\":\"([^\"]+)\"', 1, dataFields)\n   149→| extend aborted = extract(@'\"aborted\":(true|false)', 1, dataFields)\n   150→| summarize FailureCount = count(),\n   151→            AvgDurationMs = avg(durationMs)\n   152→            by failureReason, lastStage, agentId, aborted, clientAppName, clientAppPlatform, ring\n   153→| order by FailureCount desc\n   154→```\n   155→\n   156→### 2. Query ACE/ICE Rates (Overall, by Ring, by Agent×Ring)\n   157→\n   158→#### Using duration (default):\n   159→```kql\n   160→// Overall + by ring\n   161→WorkflowOperationEvent\n   162→| where operationName == \"OfficeAgentTask\"\n   163→| where TIMESTAMP > ago(1d)\n   164→| extend ring = tostring(split(Tenant, \"_\")[0])\n   165→| extend failureReason = extract(@'\"failureReason\":\"([^\"]+)\"', 1, dataFields)\n   166→| extend isExpected = failureReason in (\"AgentUnavailableForUser\", \"WorkflowAborted\", \"ConversationExpired\")\n   167→| summarize\n   168→    Total = count(),\n   169→    AllFailures = countif(success == 0),\n   170→    ActionableFailures = countif(success == 0 and not(isExpected))\n   171→    by ring\n   172→| extend ICE = round(100.0 * AllFailures / Total, 2),\n   173→         ACE = round(100.0 * ActionableFailures / Total, 2)\n   174→\n   175→// By agent x ring\n   176→WorkflowOperationEvent\n   177→| where operationName == \"OfficeAgentTask\"\n   178→| where TIMESTAMP > ago(1d)\n   179→| extend ring = tostring(split(Tenant, \"_\")[0])\n   180→| extend failureReason = extract(@'\"failureReason\":\"([^\"]+)\"', 1, dataFields)\n   181→| extend agentId = extract(@'\"agentId\":\"([^\"]+)\"', 1, dataFields)\n   182→| extend isExpected = failureReason in (\"AgentUnavailableForUser\", \"WorkflowAborted\", \"ConversationExpired\")\n   183→| where agentId in (\"PowerPoint\", \"Excel\", \"Word\")\n   184→| summarize\n   185→    Total = count(),\n   186→    AllFailures = countif(success == 0),\n   187→    ActionableFailures = countif(success == 0 and not(isExpected))\n   188→    by agentId, ring\n   189→| extend ICE = round(100.0 * AllFailures / Total, 2),\n   190→         ACE = round(100.0 * ActionableFailures / Total, 2)\n   191→```\n   192→\n   193→#### Using UTC time range:\n   194→```kql\n   195→// Overall + by ring\n   196→WorkflowOperationEvent\n   197→| where operationName == \"OfficeAgentTask\"\n   198→| where TIMESTAMP between (datetime(2026-02-01T00:00:00Z) .. datetime(2026-02-13T00:00:00Z))\n   199→| extend ring = tostring(split(Tenant, \"_\")[0])\n   200→| extend failureReason = extract(@'\"failureReason\":\"([^\"]+)\"', 1, dataFields)\n   201→| extend isExpected = failureReason in (\"AgentUnavailableForUser\", \"WorkflowAborted\", \"ConversationExpired\")\n   202→| summarize\n   203→    Total = count(),\n   204→    AllFailures = countif(success == 0),\n   205→    ActionableFailures = countif(success == 0 and not(isExpected))\n   206→    by ring\n   207→| extend ICE = round(100.0 * AllFailures / Total, 2),\n   208→         ACE = round(100.0 * ActionableFailures / Total, 2)\n   209→\n   210→// By agent x ring\n   211→WorkflowOperationEvent\n   212→| where operationName == \"OfficeAgentTask\"\n   213→| where TIMESTAMP between (datetime(2026-02-01T00:00:00Z) .. datetime(2026-02-13T00:00:00Z))\n   214→| extend ring = tostring(split(Tenant, \"_\")[0])\n   215→| extend failureReason = extract(@'\"failureReason\":\"([^\"]+)\"', 1, dataFields)\n   216→| extend agentId = extract(@'\"agentId\":\"([^\"]+)\"', 1, dataFields)\n   217→| extend isExpected = failureReason in (\"AgentUnavailableForUser\", \"WorkflowAborted\", \"ConversationExpired\")\n   218→| where agentId in (\"PowerPoint\", \"Excel\", \"Word\")\n   219→| summarize\n   220→    Total = count(),\n   221→    AllFailures = countif(success == 0),\n   222→    ActionableFailures = countif(success == 0 and not(isExpected))\n   223→    by agentId, ring\n   224→| extend ICE = round(100.0 * AllFailures / Total, 2),\n   225→         ACE = round(100.0 * ActionableFailures / Total, 2)\n   226→```\n   227→\n   228→### 3. Cross-Reference with ADO\n   229→Search ADO for each failure reason to find existing bugs:\n   230→- Search terms: `OneDriveUploadFailed`, `MipLabelApplicationFailed`, `WebSocketClosed`, `TaskFailed`, `AgentBusy`, `DocumentContentValidationFailed`, `UnknownError`, `InitializationFailed`, `InvalidQuery`\n   231→- Search broadly (without `OfficeAgentTask` prefix) as bugs may use different naming\n   232→- Project: `OC` in the `Office` organization\n   233→\n   234→### 4. Write Input JSON and Run Script\n   235→After collecting all data from steps 1-3, write the results to a JSON file matching the input schema above, then run:\n   236→```powershell\n   237→python .github\\skills\\office-agent-failure-analysis\\generate_report.py <input_json_path> <output_html_path>\n   238→```\n   239→\n   240→The `failures` array needs at minimum `FailureCount`, `agentId`, `failureReason`, and `ring` per entry.\n   241→The `ado_items` object maps each actionable failure reason to an array of ADO work items (empty array if none found).\n   242→\n   243→### 5. Open in Browser\n   244→```powershell\n   245→Start-Process \"path\\to\\report.html\"\n   246→```\n   247→\n   248→## Output\n   249→- HTML file: `OfficeAgentTask_Failures_Report.html` (default name)\n   250→- Opens automatically in default browser\n   251→\n   252→## Key Metrics Definitions\n   253→- **ACE (Actionable Customer Errors)**: `ActionableFailures / TotalOperations × 100` — excludes expected errors\n   254→- **ICE (Including all Customer Errors)**: `AllFailures / TotalOperations × 100` — includes all errors\n   255→- **Ring**: Deployment ring extracted from `Tenant` field — `dogfood` → `msit` → `prod`\n   256→- **ADO Coverage**: Percentage of actionable failures that have corresponding ADO work items\n   257→\n   258→## Notes\n   259→- Time range defaults to `ago(1d)` but can be adjusted per user request using duration in days or UTC time ranges\n   260→- The `time_range` field in the input JSON supports two formats:\n   261→  - `{\"type\": \"duration\", \"duration_days\": 7}` — for relative lookback (e.g., last 7 days)\n   262→  - `{\"type\": \"range\", \"start\": \"2026-02-01T00:00:00Z\", \"end\": \"2026-02-13T00:00:00Z\"}` — for explicit UTC time range\n   263→- If `time_range` is omitted, the report defaults to \"Last 24 hours\"\n   264→- `dataFields` is a JSON string — use `extract()` with regex to parse fields\n   265→- Ring is the first segment of `Tenant` before `_`\n   266→- Always check for both `success == 0` and parse `failureReason` from `dataFields`\n   267→- When searching ADO, try multiple search term variations as bug titles vary\n   268→- The report color scheme uses CSS custom properties for consistent dark theme\n   269→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JgzknBttobEMZ4qK1jH68n","session_id":"059c34c4-4758-4e2f-87ba-9357713e7c91","uuid":"b889ca15-44b0-4c61-bebd-49d7312318bf"}
