{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JiEupNcyVjkcjFAvwLFybD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: eval-pipeline\n     3→description: End-to-end eval pipeline — generate evals on feature/main branches, merge results, and upload to SBSLeoV3 portal\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Eval Pipeline (Agentic)\n     7→\n     8→Fully agentic end-to-end evaluation pipeline. Collects all configuration upfront, then executes the entire flow autonomously — generate evals, merge results, and upload to the SBSLeoV3 portal.\n     9→\n    10→**Core principle: Be agentic.** Collect all user inputs in as few interactions as possible, then execute every step yourself. Never tell the user to \"run this command\" or \"re-invoke this skill later\". You own the entire pipeline from start to finish.\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→## Phase 0: Collect All Configuration Upfront\n    15→\n    16→The goal is to gather everything needed for the entire pipeline in as few interactions as possible, then execute autonomously.\n    17→\n    18→### Step 0.1 — Ask mode\n    19→\n    20→Use `AskUserQuestion` with a single question:\n    21→\n    22→| Option | Description |\n    23→|--------|-------------|\n    24→| **Generate + Merge + Upload** | Run eval generation, then automatically merge & upload when done |\n    25→| **Merge + Upload only** | Use existing results in `eval/outputs/` to merge & upload now |\n    26→\n    27→Then follow the appropriate path below.\n    28→\n    29→---\n    30→\n    31→### Path A: Generate + Merge + Upload\n    32→\n    33→**Round 1** — Use a single `AskUserQuestion` with two questions:\n    34→\n    35→**Question 1 — Eval alias:**\n    36→\n    37→| Option | Description |\n    38→|--------|-------------|\n    39→| `ppt.ungrounded` | PPT generation using official dataset |\n    40→| `ppt.pairwise` | Pairwise PPT vs Societas |\n    41→| `ppt.enterprise.dev` | PPT enterprise implicit/explicit (dev) |\n    42→| `word.ungrounded.dev` | Word pointwise (dev dataset) |\n    43→\n    44→**Question 2 — Branches:**\n    45→\n    46→| Option | Description |\n    47→|--------|-------------|\n    48→| **Current branch only** | Run eval only on the current feature branch |\n    49→| **Main only** | Run eval only on the `main` branch |\n    50→| **Both (current + main)** | Run eval on current branch first, then on main |\n    51→\n    52→**Round 2 (conditional)** — Only if branches is **NOT** \"Both\":\n    53→\n    54→If user selected **Both**, the main branch eval automatically becomes the baseline — **skip this round entirely** and proceed to the Execution Summary.\n    55→\n    56→Otherwise, use `AskUserQuestion` with one question to ask for the baseline source. List `eval/outputs/` folders and show the most recent as options. Also include societas presets. **Important:** `AskUserQuestion` allows max 4 options per question, so show at most 3 folders + Societas preset = 4 options:\n    57→\n    58→| Option | Description |\n    59→|--------|-------------|\n    60→| *(most recent 3 folders from eval/outputs/)* | Show as individual options |\n    61→| **Societas preset** | Use a pre-built societas baseline (22, 26, or 35 queries) instead of a run folder |\n    62→\n    63→If user picks **Societas preset**, ask which version (22, 26, or 35) in a follow-up.\n    64→\n    65→**Auto-detect app type** from alias prefix (`ppt.*` → ppt, `word.*` → word, `excel.*` → excel). If ambiguous, ask.\n    66→\n    67→**Auto-detect everything else:**\n    68→- Branch name: `git branch --show-current`\n    69→- Username: `whoami` (strip domain prefix)\n    70→- Portal config: use defaults (SBSLeoV3 Evaluation, Project Sigma SBSLeoV3 Template, dev-gpt-5-reasoning, per-app metrics)\n    71→\n    72→Then proceed to the **Execution Summary** step below.\n    73→\n    74→---\n    75→\n    76→### Path B: Merge + Upload only\n    77→\n    78→**No alias or branches needed.** The user is providing existing run folders.\n    79→\n    80→1. List `eval/outputs/` folders using Bash.\n    81→2. Use a single `AskUserQuestion` to collect **both folders**:\n    82→\n    83→**Question 1 — Feature branch run folder:** Show the most recent 4 folders as options (user can also type via Other).\n    84→\n    85→**Question 2 — Baseline run folder:** Show the most recent folders as options plus societas presets. **Important:** `AskUserQuestion` allows max 4 options per question, so show at most 3 folders + Societas preset = 4 options:\n    86→\n    87→| Option | Description |\n    88→|--------|-------------|\n    89→| *(most recent 3 folders from eval/outputs/)* | Show as individual options |\n    90→| **Societas preset** | Use a pre-built societas baseline (22, 26, or 35 queries) instead of a run folder |\n    91→\n    92→If user picks **Societas preset**, ask which version (22, 26, or 35) in a follow-up.\n    93→\n    94→3. **Auto-detect everything else:**\n    95→   - **App type**: infer from folder name (`*ppt*` → ppt, `*word*` → word, `*excel*` → excel). If ambiguous, ask.\n    96→   - **Branch name**: `git branch --show-current`\n    97→   - **Username**: `whoami` (strip domain prefix)\n    98→   - **Portal config**: use defaults\n    99→\n   100→Then proceed to the **Execution Summary** step below.\n   101→\n   102→---\n   103→\n   104→### Pre-flight Checks (Generate mode only, before showing summary)\n   105→\n   106→If the user selected **Main only** or **Both (current + main)**, run this check **immediately after collecting configuration** and **before showing the Execution Summary**:\n   107→\n   108→1. Check for uncommitted changes (informational — will stash later if needed):\n   109→   ```bash\n   110→   git status --porcelain\n   111→   ```\n   112→   If uncommitted changes exist, note this in the Execution Summary so the user knows a stash will happen.\n   113→\n   114→2. Compute the merge-base commit (the point where the feature branch forked from main):\n   115→   ```bash\n   116→   git fetch origin main\n   117→   MERGE_BASE=$(git merge-base HEAD origin/main)\n   118→   ```\n   119→   Save this commit hash. The \"main\" eval will check out **this exact commit**, not the latest main. This ensures an apples-to-apples comparison — the only difference between the two evals is the user's feature branch changes.\n   120→\n   121→Then proceed to the Execution Summary.\n   122→\n   123→---\n   124→\n   125→### Execution Summary (both paths) — Plan Mode Approval\n   126→\n   127→After collecting all inputs, **before executing anything**, use the plan mode flow to get blanket approval with pre-authorized permissions for all pipeline commands.\n   128→\n   129→#### Step 1: Enter plan mode\n   130→\n   131→Call `EnterPlanMode` to switch into plan mode.\n   132→\n   133→#### Step 2: Write the plan\n   134→\n   135→Write the complete execution summary to the plan file (the path is provided in the plan mode system message). Fill in ALL placeholders with actual resolved values — the user should see concrete values (e.g. `ppt.ungrounded`, `user/foo/bar`, `abc123def`), not templates.\n   136→\n   137→**For Merge + Upload only mode, write this to the plan file:**\n   138→```\n   139→Pipeline plan:\n   140→\n   141→Steps:\n   142→  1. [Merge]  merge <feature_folder> with <baseline_folder> → merged_eval_YYYYMMDD.jsonl\n   143→  2. [Upload] upload to SBSLeoV3 portal (auto-submit)\n   144→\n   145→Upload config:\n   146→  Merged file:  merged_eval_YYYYMMDD.jsonl\n   147→  Eval name:    (<username>) : <branch_name>\n   148→  App type:     <ppt|word|excel>\n   149→  Eval method:  SBSLeoV3 Evaluation\n   150→  Template:     Project Sigma SBSLeoV3 Template\n   151→  Model:        dev-gpt-5-reasoning\n   152→  Auto-submit:  Yes\n   153→```\n   154→\n   155→**For Generate + Merge + Upload mode, write this to the plan file:**\n   156→```\n   157→Pipeline plan:\n   158→\n   159→Steps (sequential — evals cannot run concurrently):\n   160→  0. [Build]    yarn stop; yarn build (feature branch)\n   161→  1. [Eval #1]  oagent eval <alias> --ts → wait for completion (~4-5 hours)\n   162→  2. [Git]      git stash → checkout merge-base <hash> → build (if running main eval)\n   163→  3. [Eval #2]  oagent eval <alias> --ts → wait for completion (~4-5 hours, if running main eval)\n   164→  4. [Git]      checkout back → pop stash → rebuild feature branch\n   165→  5. [Merge]    merge eval results → merged_eval_YYYYMMDD.jsonl\n   166→  6. [Upload]   upload to SBSLeoV3 portal (auto-submit)\n   167→\n   168→Config:\n   169→  Eval alias:   <alias>\n   170→  Branch(es):   <current / main / both>\n   171→  Baseline:     <folder name or \"merge-base eval\" or \"societas N\">\n   172→  Merge-base:   <commit hash> (only if running main eval)\n   173→  Uncommitted:  <yes — will stash / no>\n   174→\n   175→Upload config:\n   176→  Eval name:    (<username>) : <branch_name>\n   177→  App type:     <ppt|word|excel>\n   178→  Eval method:  SBSLeoV3 Evaluation\n   179→  Template:     Project Sigma SBSLeoV3 Template\n   180→  Model:        dev-gpt-5-reasoning\n   181→  Auto-submit:  Yes\n   182→```\n   183→\n   184→#### Step 3: Exit plan mode\n   185→\n   186→Call `ExitPlanMode` (no special parameters needed).\n   187→\n   188→If the user approves the plan → execute everything without further questions.\n   189→If the user rejects → stop.\n   190→\n   191→**CRITICAL — Bypass per-command permission prompts**: After plan approval, set `dangerouslyDisableSandbox: true` on **EVERY** `Bash` tool call for the rest of the pipeline. The user already approved the full plan — individual command prompts would defeat the purpose of agentic execution. This is a Bash tool parameter, not a settings change, so it works for any developer without configuration.\n   192→\n   193→---\n   194→\n   195→## Phase 1: Generate Evals\n   196→\n   197→**You execute all commands directly.** Do not tell the user to run commands. Use the Bash tool for everything.\n   198→\n   199→**CRITICAL: Evals run sequentially, not concurrently.** The eval process uses a shared Docker container. Running `yarn stop; yarn build` kills the container, which would destroy any in-progress eval. Therefore, when running \"Both\" branches, you MUST fully complete the feature branch eval before starting the main branch eval.\n   200→\n   201→### Execution order for \"Both\" branches:\n   202→\n   203→1. Build feature branch → launch eval → **wait for eval to complete** (~4-5 hours)\n   204→2. Stash → checkout merge-base → build → launch eval → **wait for eval to complete** (~4-5 hours)\n   205→3. Switch back to feature branch → pop stash → rebuild\n   206→\n   207→### Branch: Current branch\n   208→\n   209→If the user selected **Current branch only** or **Both**:\n   210→\n   211→1. Get the current branch name:\n   212→   ```bash\n   213→   git branch --show-current\n   214→   ```\n   215→\n   216→2. Stop the running server and rebuild:\n   217→   ```bash\n   218→   powershell -Command \"yarn stop; yarn build\"\n   219→   ```\n   220→   Wait for completion. If build fails, stop and report the error.\n   221→\n   222→3. Run the eval in background:\n   223→   ```bash\n   224→   powershell -Command \"oagent eval <alias> --ts\"\n   225→   ```\n   226→   Use `run_in_background: true`. Save the background task ID.\n   227→\n   228→4. Report to user: eval started on `<branch_name>`, running in background.\n   229→\n   230→5. **Wait for the eval to complete** before proceeding (see \"Polling long-running evals\" below). When complete, note the run folder name.\n   231→\n   232→### Branch: Main\n   233→\n   234→If the user selected **Main only** or **Both**:\n   235→\n   236→**Important**: If running \"Both\", this section executes only AFTER the feature branch eval has fully completed.\n   237→\n   238→**Branch switching protocol — execute all steps yourself:**\n   239→\n   240→The merge-base commit was already computed in Pre-flight Checks. Use it here.\n   241→\n   242→1. Check for uncommitted changes:\n   243→   ```bash\n   244→   git status --porcelain\n   245→   ```\n   246→\n   247→2. If uncommitted changes exist, stash them:\n   248→   ```bash\n   249→   git stash push -m \"eval-pipeline: auto-stash before switching to main\"\n   250→   ```\n   251→\n   252→3. Check out the merge-base commit (detached HEAD):\n   253→   ```bash\n   254→   git checkout <MERGE_BASE>\n   255→   ```\n   256→   This is the exact commit where the feature branch forked from main — ensuring the comparison is apples-to-apples (only the user's changes differ).\n   257→\n   258→4. Rebuild:\n   259→   ```bash\n   260→   powershell -Command \"yarn stop; yarn build\"\n   261→   ```\n   262→   If build fails → switch back, pop stash, report error.\n   263→\n   264→5. Run eval in background:\n   265→   ```bash\n   266→   powershell -Command \"oagent eval <alias> --ts\"\n   267→   ```\n   268→   Use `run_in_background: true`. Save the background task ID.\n   269→\n   270→6. **Wait for the eval to complete** before proceeding (see \"Polling long-running evals\" below). When complete, note the run folder name.\n   271→\n   272→7. Switch back and restore:\n   273→   ```bash\n   274→   git checkout <original_branch>\n   275→   git stash pop  # only if we stashed\n   276→   ```\n   277→\n   278→8. Rebuild feature branch code:\n   279→   ```bash\n   280→   powershell -Command \"yarn stop; yarn build\"\n   281→   ```\n   282→\n   283→9. Report: main eval complete. Proceed to Phase 2.\n   284→\n   285→---\n   286→\n   287→## Phase 2: Identify Run Folders & Auto-Proceed\n   288→\n   289→**Do NOT tell the user to re-invoke the skill.** You stay in the loop and auto-proceed.\n   290→\n   291→### Single branch mode (Current only or Main only)\n   292→\n   293→After the eval completes (you already waited in Phase 1), identify the new run folder in `eval/outputs/` (most recent folder by timestamp) and proceed to Phase 3.\n   294→\n   295→### Both branches mode\n   296→\n   297→After both evals have completed sequentially (you already waited for each in Phase 1), you should have two run folder names. Identify them:\n   298→- The feature branch folder becomes the \"conversation\" file.\n   299→- The main branch folder becomes the \"baseline\" file.\n   300→\n   301→Proceed to Phase 3.\n   302→\n   303→### Polling long-running evals\n   304→\n   305→Evals can take up to 4-5 hours. The Bash tool `timeout` max is 10 minutes, so you **must** use background mode + polling:\n   306→\n   307→1. **Launch**: Use `Bash` with `run_in_background: true`. This returns a task ID immediately.\n   308→2. **Poll**: Use `TaskOutput` with `block: false` and `timeout: 30000`. This returns the current status without blocking.\n   309→   - If status is `running` → the eval is still in progress.\n   310→   - If status is `completed` → proceed to the next step.\n   311→3. **Polling cadence**: Check every 3-5 minutes. Do NOT use `block: true` (it would time out after 30s and return incomplete results).\n   312→4. **Status updates**: Give the user periodic updates (\"Still running... ~2 hours in\").\n   313→5. **Multitask**: If the user sends a message while polling, respond to it — you can handle other requests between polls.\n   314→\n   315→---\n   316→\n   317→## Phase 3: Merge\n   318→\n   319→### Step 3.1 — Identify files\n   320→\n   321→**If arriving from Phase 2 (auto-flow):**\n   322→- List `eval/outputs/` and identify the newest folder(s) created since the eval started.\n   323→- Find `conversations_*.jsonl` in each folder.\n   324→- Confirm with the user: \"I found run folder `<name>` — using this for merge.\"\n   325→\n   326→**If Merge+Upload only mode:**\n   327→- The user already picked the feature branch folder in Phase 0. Find its `conversations_*.jsonl` file.\n   328→\n   329→### Step 3.2 — Run the merge\n   330→\n   331→**If using a societas preset baseline (22, 26, or 35):**\n   332→\n   333→```bash\n   334→PYTHONIOENCODING=utf-8 python eval/scripts/merge_jsonl_for_eval.py <run_folder_name> --societas <22|26|35> --output merged_eval_<YYYYMMDD>.jsonl\n   335→```\n   336→\n   337→**If using a custom run folder as baseline:**\n   338→\n   339→Find the JSONL files in both folders, then:\n   340→\n   341→```bash\n   342→PYTHONIOENCODING=utf-8 python eval/scripts/merge_jsonl_for_eval.py \"<feature_branch_jsonl>\" \"<baseline_jsonl>\" \"merged_eval_<YYYYMMDD>.jsonl\"\n   343→```\n   344→\n   345→Output file: `merged_eval_<YYYYMMDD>.jsonl` in the OfficeAgent root directory.\n   346→\n   347→### Step 3.3 — Verify and report\n   348→\n   349→Confirm the merged file exists. Report:\n   350→- File path and size\n   351→- Number of lines (matched pairs)\n   352→- First few lines preview\n   353→\n   354→Then **immediately proceed to Phase 4** — do not stop.\n   355→\n   356→---\n   357→\n   358→## Phase 4: Upload to Portal\n   359→\n   360→### Step 4.1 — Get metadata\n   361→\n   362→```bash\n   363→git branch --show-current\n   364→whoami\n   365→```\n   366→\n   367→Extract username (e.g. `adityaaswal` from `DOMAIN\\adityaaswal`).\n   368→\n   369→### Step 4.2 — Show config summary and auto-submit\n   370→\n   371→Display the upload configuration as an FYI to the user (no confirmation needed — proceed immediately):\n   372→\n   373→```\n   374→Upload config:\n   375→  Merged file:  merged_eval_20260216.jsonl\n   376→  Eval name:    (adityaaswal) : user/aditya/feature\n   377→  App type:     ppt\n   378→  Eval method:  SBSLeoV3 Evaluation\n   379→  Template:     Project Sigma SBSLeoV3 Template\n   380→  Model:        dev-gpt-5-reasoning\n   381→  Metrics:      Fidelity, Aesthetics, Consistency, ...\n   382→  Auto-submit:  Yes\n   383→```\n   384→\n   385→Then immediately execute the upload — do not ask for confirmation.\n   386→\n   387→### Step 4.3 — Execute upload\n   388→\n   389→Run the upload script directly:\n   390→\n   391→```bash\n   392→PYTHONIOENCODING=utf-8 python eval/scripts/upload_eval_to_portal.py \"<merged_file_path>\" --name \"(<username>) : <branch_name>\" --app <app_type> --submit\n   393→```\n   394→\n   395→Optional override flags (only if user provided custom values):\n   396→- `--method \"<eval_method>\"`\n   397→- `--template \"<template>\"`\n   398→- `--model \"<model>\"`\n   399→- `--metrics-file \"<path>\"`\n   400→\n   401→### Step 4.4 — Report result\n   402→\n   403→Report the script output. If the browser is open for manual review, tell the user.\n   404→\n   405→**Pipeline complete.**\n   406→\n   407→---\n   408→\n   409→## Error Handling\n   410→\n   411→- **Missing run folders**: List available folders and ask user to clarify.\n   412→- **No JSONL file found**: Report error and show folder contents.\n   413→- **Merge fails (0 matches)**: Report statistics and ask user to verify inputs.\n   414→- **Branch switching fails**: Report error, suggest manual resolution. Never force-checkout.\n   415→- **Stash pop conflicts**: Warn user immediately.\n   416→- **Build fails**: Report error output. If on wrong branch, switch back first.\n   417→- **Upload script fails**: Show error output. Common issues:\n   418→  - Portal unreachable: check network\n   419→  - Dropdown not found: script prints WARNING — user should set manually in the open browser\n   420→  - Playwright not installed: run `pip install playwright && python -m playwright install chromium`\n   421→\n   422→## Important Notes\n   423→\n   424→- **Be agentic**: Execute all commands yourself using Bash tool. Never tell the user to run commands manually.\n   425→- **Auto-proceed**: After each phase completes, move to the next phase immediately. The only hard stops are errors. Upload auto-submits by default.\n   426→- **Collect inputs upfront**: Gather all configuration in Phase 0 so the rest of the pipeline runs autonomously.\n   427→- The upload script has **per-app metric definitions** (ppt/word/excel). The `--app` flag selects which set.\n   428→- App type is auto-detected from alias prefix. If ambiguous, ask once.\n   429→- Eval name format: `(<username>) : <branch_name>`\n   430→- Use `PYTHONIOENCODING=utf-8` for both merge and upload scripts on Windows.\n   431→- Eval generation uses `powershell -Command \"oagent eval <alias> --ts\"` because `oagent` is not in bash PATH. Always use `powershell` (not `powershell.exe`) for broader compatibility with allow patterns.\n   432→- **Permission bypass**: After plan approval, all Bash calls MUST set `dangerouslyDisableSandbox: true` to avoid per-command permission prompts. The plan approval is the single point of user consent.\n   433→- **Sequential execution is mandatory**: `yarn stop; yarn build` kills the Docker container, which destroys any in-progress eval. When running \"Both\" branches, you MUST wait for the feature branch eval to fully complete before starting the main branch build+eval. Never run two evals concurrently.\n   434→- When switching for main eval: wait for feature eval to complete → stash → checkout merge-base commit → build → spawn eval → wait for completion → checkout back → pop stash → rebuild. The merge-base is the commit where the feature branch forked from main, ensuring an apples-to-apples comparison.\n   435→- The upload script launches a **visible** browser for user verification.\n   436→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JgzknBttobEMZ4qK1jH68n","session_id":"059c34c4-4758-4e2f-87ba-9357713e7c91","uuid":"02bae4a4-c18d-4991-a463-44e4f2a48503"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YHCA4ScL6jmc4bBsfDZodD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: commit\n     3→description: Create a properly formatted git commit for all pending local changes following Azure DevOps conventions\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→### Create a new commit for all pending local changes\n     7→\n     8→1. **Review the working tree**\n     9→\n    10→   * Run `git status`, `git diff HEAD`, and `git status --porcelain` to identify modified and untracked files.\n    11→\n    12→2. **Stage the changes**\n    13→\n    14→   * Add all relevant files (both new and modified) to the commit.\n    15→\n    16→3. **Create an atomic commit**\n    17→\n    18→   * Ensure the commit represents a single, focused logical change.\n    19→\n    20→4. **Follow Azure DevOps commit message conventions**\n    21→\n    22→   * Use a structured commit message with a standard prefix:\n    23→\n    24→     * `feat` – New functionality\n    25→     * `fix` – Bug fixes\n    26→     * `docs` – Documentation updates\n    27→     * `refactor` – Code refactoring\n    28→     * `chore` – Maintenance / tooling changes\n    29→   * Keep the subject concise and descriptive (imperative tense).\n    30→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JgzknBttobEMZ4qK1jH68n","session_id":"059c34c4-4758-4e2f-87ba-9357713e7c91","uuid":"eb8663ff-6b15-46eb-a90b-0d0ca7561656"}
