{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JgzknBttobEMZ4qK1jH68n","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information about the infrastructure layer. Let me compile a structured summary for you.\n\n## Infrastructure Layer Exploration Summary\n\n### 1. Docker Setup and Runtime Environment\n\n**Dockerfile (docker/Dockerfile)**\n- Multi-stage build optimizing image size and build cache efficiency\n- Base image: `mcr.microsoft.com/officepy/codeexecutionjupyter4:16.0.19909.43250` (OfficePy-based)\n- Key build stages:\n  - **Poppler builder**: Compiles PDF processing library from source (poppler-26.02.0) with minimal dependencies\n  - **LibreOffice installer**: Extracts and installs LibreOffice 26.2.0 RPMs for document processing\n  - **Node dependencies**: npm 24 with caching (mounted at `/root/.npm`)\n  - **Final runtime**: Assembles outputs from builders with OfficePy base\n- Environment variables: \n  - `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_OUTPUT_TOKENS=64000`\n  - `NODE_PATH` points to `/app/node_modules` and `/app/api/node_modules`\n\n**Docker runtime dependencies (docker/package.json)**\n- Node 22.0.0+ required\n- Key packages:\n  - Claude Agent SDK (`@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` v0.2.39)\n  - Office document generation: docx, pptxgenjs, sharp\n  - Browser automation: Playwright 1.57.0\n  - Web: Express 4.19.2, WebSocket, TypeScript 5.9.3\n  - GitHub Copilot SDK integration\n  - MCP (Model Context Protocol) SDK 1.26.0\n  - Chart.js for visualizations\n  - React 19.2.1 (frontend components)\n\n**Docker Compose (docker-compose.yml)**\n- Service: `officeagent` container with dynamic port mapping\n- Ports exposed: 6010 (external API), 6011 (internal), 6020 (Node debug), 7010 (grounding agent HTTP)\n- Health check: `curl http://localhost:6010/health` (10s interval, 5s timeout, 5 retries)\n- Environment variables for OfficePy configuration, file uploads, agent ID selection\n- Network: Bridge network `officeagent-net`\n- Supports horizontal scaling (e.g., `docker compose up -d --scale officeagent=3`)\n- Optional: load balancer config (`docker-compose.loadbalancer.yml`) and Lumina alternative image\n\n---\n\n### 2. Eval Framework Structure\n\n**Purpose**: Python-based evaluation framework using pytest for automated testing of Office document generation\n\n**Entry point**: `/eval/CLAUDE.md` with quick reference guide\n\n**Directory structure** (`eval/` 2 levels deep):\n```\neval/\n├── aliases.json                    # Named eval aliases\n├── CLAUDE.md                       # Quick reference docs\n├── configs/                        # Eval configuration JSON files\n│   ├── cq_leo/                     # Clarification query configs\n│   ├── dev/                        # Development loop configs\n│   └── *.json                      # Document-type configs\n├── datasets/                       # Test batch files (JSON)\n├── src/                            # Python implementation\n│   ├── cli.py                      # CLI entry point (oagent eval)\n│   ├── framework.py                # Main orchestrator\n│   ├── types.py                    # EvalRequest/EvalConfig/EvalResult\n│   ├── evaluators/                 # Modular evaluators\n│   ├── preprocessors/              # Data extraction\n│   ├── scrapers/                   # API-based document generation\n│   └── utils/                      # Shared utilities\n├── prompt_templates/               # LLM evaluation prompts\n├── scripts/\n│   ├── xlsx/perf/                  # Excel A/B testing\n│   └── pptx/                       # PPT batch generation\n├── experiments/                    # Experimental evals\n├── .claude/\n│   ├── agents/prompt-to-excel.md   # Custom agent for Excel evals\n│   ├── settings.json               # Configuration\n│   └── settings.local.json         # Local overrides\n└── outputs/                        # Generated results (gitignored)\n```\n\n**Key evaluators**:\n- `excel` — 1-5 scale: accuracy, completeness, usefulness, reliability, aesthetics\n- `pairwise` — Side-by-side comparison (uses ExcelComparisonHelper for xlsx)\n- `societas` — Visual quality (fidelity, aesthetics, consistency, storytelling)\n- `content` — Content quality\n- `rule_based` — Deterministic rules (PPT slide count, bullets)\n- `intent` — Artifact generation intent detection\n\n**Output structure**:\n```\neval/outputs/<run_name>/\n├── eval_report_<run_name>_<timestamp>.json   # Aggregate\n└── <test_id>/<app_name>/                     # Default: \"officeagent\"\n    ├── doc/                                  # Generated documents\n    │   ├── *.xlsx / *.pptx / *.docx\n    │   ├── scrape_result.json                # Generation outcome\n    │   └── debug/logs/officeagent.log        # Agent logs\n    └── eval/                                 # Evaluation results\n        └── excel_result_run1.json            # Consolidated results\n```\n\n**Config defaults**: API port 6010, timeout 1800s, evaluation model `dev-gpt-5-reasoning`\n\n**CLI usage**:\n```powershell\noagent eval alias                                    # List aliases\noagent eval ppt.example                              # Quick smoke test\noagent eval ppt.groundingeval -n 3                   # First 3 tests\noagent eval submit --prompt \"Create...\" --type pptx  # Single submission\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. CLI Tool Capabilities (.devtools/cli)\n\n**Package**: `@officeagent-tools/cli` v1.1.1130\n\n**Binary**: `oagent` command available in PowerShell\n\n**Key dependencies**:\n- Commander for CLI parsing\n- Chalk for colored output\n- Inquirer for interactive prompts\n- ora for spinners/loading indicators\n- table for formatted output\n- extract-zip for archive handling\n- open for launching browsers\n\n**CLI commands** (inferred from structure):\n```powershell\noagent ping                          # Health check\noagent gen \"<prompt>\" --open         # Generate and open document\noagent gen \"<prompt>\" -f flag1 flag2 # Generate with flight flags\noagent config get                    # View configuration\noagent eval alias                    # List eval aliases\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Build Pipeline (Lage + Gulp)\n\n**Lage config** (`lage.config.js`):\n- Task runner for monorepo build orchestration\n- Package manager: Yarn 4.10.3\n- Defined tasks:\n  - `build` — Compiles src/ to dist/ (depends on `^build` from dependencies)\n  - `clean` — Remove artifacts\n  - `lint` — ESLint checks\n  - `lint:fix` — Auto-fix linting issues\n  - `test` — Run tests\n- Caching inputs: `src/**`, `tsconfig.json`, `package.json`, `pyproject.toml`\n- Cache invalidation: Changes to root `.js`, `.json`, `.mjs`, `.toml`, `.ini` files\n\n**Gulp tasks** (`gulpfile.mjs`):\n- Imported from `./gulp-tasks/` directory\n- Main exported tasks:\n  - `start()` — Start Docker container + test server\n  - `stop()` — Stop and remove Docker container\n  - `reload()` — Hot-deploy built files into running container\n  - `startDocker()` — Start Docker (requires local AugLoop)\n  - `startTest()` — Start test client\n  - `startMock()` — Start Docker + mock test client\n  - `startCompose()` — Docker Compose (Token Server + OfficeAgent + Test Clients)\n  - `startComposeLumina()` — Docker Compose with Lumina image\n  - `startLumina()` — Lumina container + test client\n  - `startLuminaDocker()` — Lumina container only\n  - `startLuminaMock()` — Lumina container + mock test client\n  - `stopCompose()` — Stop Docker Compose services\n  - `cleanOutputDirs()` — Clean output directories\n  - `setupDebugLinks()` — Configure debug linking\n  - `setupPythonEnvironment()` — Setup Python runtime\n  - `updateDatasetVersions()` — Dataset version management\n\n**Build integration**: `yarn build` triggers lage, which compiles TypeScript and Docker image. `yarn rebuild` cleans then builds.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Claude Skills and Commands\n\nLocated in `.claude/` directory structure:\n\n**Skills** (`.claude/skills/`):\n1. **analyze-pr** — Full PR analysis from Azure DevOps URLs\n   - Fetches PR metadata, commit history, file-by-file diffs\n   - Generates markdown reports with impact analysis\n   - Saves to `.claude/skills/analyze-pr/output/`\n\n2. **office-agent-failure-analysis** — Kusto-based failure reporting\n   - Queries OfficeAgentTask failures from ODX AugLoop Service\n   - Cross-references with ADO work items\n   - Generates styled HTML reports with ACE/ICE error rate projections\n   - Supports ring-level (dogfood, msit, prod) breakdowns\n\n3. **prompt-lint** — LLM prompt quality analysis\n   - References Opus 4.6 model configs\n\n4. **ocv-triage** — OCV (Office Code Validation) investigation\n   - Kusto queries for triage workflow\n   - Analysis and report templates\n\n5. **wxp-agent-testing** — WXP agent testing framework\n   - Multi-turn testing guide\n   - Error handling documentation\n   - Kusto investigation guide\n\n**Commands** (`.claude/commands/`):\n1. **analyze-ocv** — OCV analysis workflow\n2. **commit** — Azure DevOps-style commit message formatting\n3. **eval-pipeline** — End-to-end agentic eval pipeline\n   - Generate evals on feature/main branches\n   - Merge results and upload to SBSLeoV3 portal\n   - Fully autonomous (no manual re-invocation needed)\n4. **generate-doc** — Document generation CLI\n5. **word-eval** — Word-specific evaluation workflows\n\n**Eval-specific skills** (`eval/.claude/agents/`):\n- **prompt-to-excel.md** — Custom agent for Excel prompt evaluation\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Layer | Technology | Key Components |\n|-------|-----------|-----------------|\n| **Container Runtime** | Docker + Docker Compose | OfficePy base, LibreOffice 26.2, Node 24, Poppler PDF |\n| **API Framework** | Express 4.19.2, WebSocket | Ports 6010 (API), 6011 (internal), 6020 (debug), 7010 (grounding) |\n| **Document Generation** | docx, pptxgenjs, Playwright | DOCX, PPTX, XLSX creation and preview |\n| **AI/Agent SDK** | Claude Agent SDK 0.2.39, MCP 1.26 | Agentic workflow execution, tool integration |\n| **Automation & Build** | Yarn 4.10.3, Lage, Gulp | Task orchestration, hot-reload, Docker build |\n| **Evaluation** | Python pytest, custom evaluators | 6+ evaluator types, Kusto integration, SBSLeoV3 portal upload |\n| **CLI Tool** | Commander, Chalk, Inquirer | `oagent` command for eval, config, document generation |\n| **Development Tools** | Claude skills/commands (5+ skills) | PR analysis, failure analysis, eval pipeline automation, linting |\n\n---\n\n**Absolute file paths referenced**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/docker/Dockerfile`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/docker/package.json`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/docker-compose.yml`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/eval/CLAUDE.md`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/.devtools/cli/package.json`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/lage.config.js`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/gulpfile.mjs`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/.claude/skills/` (5 skills: analyze-pr, office-agent-failure-analysis, prompt-lint, ocv-triage, wxp-agent-testing)\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/.claude/commands/` (5 commands: analyze-ocv, commit, eval-pipeline, generate-doc, word-eval)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a34000ca7e4bdf09a (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 55575\ntool_uses: 16\nduration_ms: 56704</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"059c34c4-4758-4e2f-87ba-9357713e7c91","uuid":"347c1d2a-d9b9-4999-97ca-6dd6254d8760","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the OfficeAgent repo at C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent. Do a \"medium\" exploration of the infrastructure layer:\n\n1. Read `docker/Dockerfile` (first 100 lines)\n2. Read `docker/package.json`\n3. Read `docker-compose.yml`\n4. Read `eval/CLAUDE.md`\n5. List `eval/` directory structure (2 levels deep)\n6. Read `.devtools/cli/package.json` to understand the CLI tool\n7. Read `lage.config.js` to understand build pipeline\n8. Read `gulpfile.mjs` to understand task definitions\n9. Check `.clau