{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KSeZHbzZfZijmj8zzLxfx9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: Word Document Suite\n     3→description: Microsoft Word (.docx) document creation with intelligent content generation, themed formatting, and chart integration. It generates professional reports, proposals, and documents with automatic validation. This should be used when users need to work with Word documents for (1) Creating new .docx files with professional formatting and themed styling, (2) Generating reports, proposals, or business documents, (3) Creating documents from outlines or requirements, (4) Documents requiring charts and tables, or (5) multi-section documents with Table of Contents and References, or (6) Company or enterprise data such as user documents, past week emails etc\n     4→locale: queryLocale\n     5→---\n     6→\n     7→# Word Document Suite\n     8→\n     9→You are Office Agent, a professional Word document generator.\n    10→\n    11→## Decision Logic\n    12→\n    13→Determine the appropriate workflow based on user intent:\n    14→\n    15→**CREATE (New Document)** - Use when:\n    16→- User says \"create\", \"new\", \"make\", or \"generate\" document\n    17→- User specifies a topic (e.g., \"Create report about AI\")\n    18→- First turn in conversation, OR user wants to start fresh\n    19→\n    20→**UPDATE (Modify Existing)** - Use when:\n    21→- User says \"change\", \"update\", \"modify\", \"add sections\", \"remove\", \"switch theme\"\n    22→- User references existing document (e.g., \"change the theme to metropolitan\")\n    23→- Continuation of previous document work (multi-turn context)\n    24→\n    25→## Workflow Selection\n    26→\n    27→Based on the scenario above:\n    28→\n    29→### For CREATE scenarios:\n    30→\n    31→Continue reading this file for the complete 5-phase creation workflow.\n    32→\n    33→**What you'll find:**\n    34→- 5-phase workflow (Requirements → Outline → Sections → DOCX → Delivery)\n    35→- Theme selection and requirements gathering\n    36→- Research-backed outline generation via @docx-outline-generator\n    37→- Parallel section creation via @docx-section-generator\n    38→- JSON to DOCX conversion process\n    39→- Final delivery formatting\n    40→\n    41→### For UPDATE scenarios:\n    42→\n    43→Read the complete update workflow: [update.md](./update.md)\n    44→\n    45→**What you'll find:**\n    46→- 7-phase workflow (Read → Update Outline → Review → Strategy → Execute → DOCX → Delivery)\n    47→- Intelligent change detection and minimal regeneration\n    48→- Theme switching and content modifications\n    49→- Strategy assignment (THEME_UPDATE, REGENERATE, REUSE, DELETE)\n    50→- Renumbering logic for deleted sections"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01VcS2pjCQDmBrQu85ZKAMvr","session_id":"059c34c4-4758-4e2f-87ba-9357713e7c91","uuid":"5514ab3d-02a4-4f23-a543-9c1b665180ec"}
