{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VcS2pjCQDmBrQu85ZKAMvr","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Structured Summary: OfficeAgent Architecture Patterns\n\n### 1. HOW AGENTS ARE STRUCTURED: Registry Pattern\n\n**Core Pattern**: Every agent exports an `AgentRegistryConfig` from `src/registry.ts` that defines:\n- **Metadata**: `id`, `name`, `packageName`, `description`\n- **Versions**: Array of `AgentVersionConfig` objects with model, tools, skills, subagents, scripts\n- **Flights**: Feature flags that override config at runtime\n- **Filters**: Rules to conditionally remove capabilities based on context\n\n**Two Types of Agents**:\n\n1. **Simple Agents** (e.g., `ppt-creation-agent`, `office-agent`):\n   - Minimal registry with only metadata\n   - Single version or no versions\n   - No skills/subagents/flights\n   - No prompt structure needed\n   - Example: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/ppt-creation-agent/src/registry.ts` (14 lines)\n\n2. **Complex Agents** (e.g., `create-agent`):\n   - Multiple versioned configurations (1.0.0, 1.1.0, 1.2.0, 1.2.1)\n   - Per-version: model, tools, skills, subagents, scripts, intent-detection prompts\n   - Multiple flights for feature experimentation\n   - Full prompt directory structure: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/<version>/`\n\n**Registry File Structure** (`AgentRegistryConfig`):\n```typescript\n{\n  id: 'create-agent',\n  name: 'Create Agent',\n  packageName: '@officeagent/create-agent',\n  description: '...',\n  defaultVersion: '1.0.0',\n  versions: [\n    {\n      version: '1.0.0',\n      model: 'claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929',\n      maxThinkingTokens: 1024,\n      maxTurns: 2000,\n      systemPrompt: './system-prompt.md',\n      raiGuidelines: './rai.md',\n      allowedTools: [...],\n      skills: ['docx', 'pptx', 'xlsx', 'image-search'],\n      subagents: ['docx-page-subagent', ...],\n      scripts: ['send-clarification-config.js', ...],\n      intentDetectionDir: ['CLARIFICATION.md', ...]\n    }\n  ],\n  flights: [\n    {\n      flightKey: 'OfficeAgent.EnableCreateAgent@1.1.0',\n      config: { version: '1.1.0' },\n      applicableVersions?: ['1.1.0']\n    }\n  ],\n  filters: []\n}\n```\n\n**Agent Base Class Hierarchy**:\n- All agents extend `BaseAgent` from `@officeagent/core`\n- Constructor receives registry\n- `initialize(context: SessionContext)` resolves config with flights and filters applied\n- `ConfigResolver.resolve()` builds final `ResolvedAgentConfig` after applying:\n  1. Version selection\n  2. Flight overrides (if enabled via `settingsManager`)\n  3. Filter rules (remove skills/subagents/tools based on context)\n\n**Example Agent Classes**:\n- `CreateAgent` extends `BaseAgent` (180+ lines of orchestration)\n- Registers hook providers (`BaseHooksProvider`, `WordHooksProvider`, `ExcelHooksProvider`, `PowerPointHooksProvider`)\n- Manages workspace, chat history, state\n\n---\n\n### 2. PROMPT ORGANIZATION: Versioned Directory Structure\n\nLocated at: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/<version>/`\n\n**Create Agent v1.1.0 Structure**:\n```\nprompts/1.1.0/\n├── system-prompt.md           # EJS-templated main prompt\n├── rai.md / rai_v1.md         # Responsible AI guidelines\n├── agent-capabilities/        # Per-document-type descriptions\n│   ├── word.md\n│   ├── excel.md\n│   └── powerpoint.md\n├── intent-detection/          # Request interceptor prompts\n│   ├── CLARIFICATION.md\n│   ├── CHAT_REPLY.md\n│   ├── INTENT_DETECTION_PROMPT.md\n│   ├── LANGUAGE_DETECTION_PROMPT.md\n│   └── PPT_CLARIFICATION.md\n├── skills/                    # 7 skills\n│   ├── docx/SKILL.md\n│   ├── pptx/SKILL.md\n│   ├── xlsx/SKILL.md\n│   ├── image-search/SKILL.md\n│   ├── pdf/SKILL.md\n│   ├── web-search/SKILL.md\n│   └── web-fetch/SKILL.md\n├── subagents/                 # 10 sub-agents\n│   ├── docx-outline-generator.md\n│   ├── docx-section-generator.md\n│   ├── pptx-outline-generator.md\n│   ├── pptx-html-creator-validator.md\n│   ├── pptx-html-updater.md\n│   ├── pptx-theme-extractor.md\n│   ├── xlsx-resource-discovery.md\n│   ├── xlsx-content-extractor.md\n│   ├── xlsx-outline-generator.md\n│   └── xlsx-office-js-generator.md\n├── scripts/                   # Runtime JS/Python scripts (30+ files)\n│   ├── web-search.js\n│   ├── enterprise-search.js\n│   ├── image-search.js\n│   ├── fetch-user-context.js\n│   └── ... (27 more)\n└── overwrites/                # Flight-conditional file replacements\n    ├── docx/\n    ├── pptx/\n    ├── xlsx/\n    └── researcher/\n```\n\n**Skill Definition** (`SKILL.md`):\n- YAML frontmatter: `name`, `description`\n- Markdown instructions with examples\n- Nested subdirectories for conversion pipelines, validation rules, themes\n- Example from docx/SKILL.md: 5-phase workflow (Requirements → Outline → Sections → DOCX → Delivery)\n\n**Sub-Agent Definition** (`.md` in `subagents/`):\n- YAML frontmatter: `name`, `description`, `tools`\n- Role description and constraints\n- Available scripts (scripts are defined once in `scripts/` and referenced)\n- Instruction sequence for the sub-agent's task\n\n---\n\n### 3. SKILLS VS SUB-AGENTS\n\n**Skills** (defined in `skills/<name>/SKILL.md`):\n- Set of instructions + scripts the main agent follows directly\n- Main agent orchestrates execution sequentially\n- Shared by all instances of the agent in the same turn\n- Example: `docx` skill guides main agent through document creation workflow\n- **When to use**: General capability the main agent needs (search, clarification, image processing)\n\n**Sub-Agents** (defined in `subagents/<name>.md`):\n- Independent Claude instances with isolated system prompt\n- Spawn separately via Task tool: `@docx-outline-generator`, `@pptx-html-creator-validator`\n- Can run in parallel\n- Own context window, tools, and model configuration\n- Example flow: `docx-outline-generator` → parallel `docx-section-generator` instances → main agent finalizes\n- **When to use**: Well-scoped pipeline step needing isolation, parallel execution, or focused context\n\n**Create Agent Pipeline Example (v1.1.0)**:\n1. Main agent determines document type and theme\n2. Spawns sub-agents in sequence/parallel:\n   - DOCX: `@docx-outline-generator` (research) → multiple `@docx-section-generator` (write sections in parallel)\n   - PPTX: `@pptx-outline-generator` → `@pptx-html-creator-validator` → `@pptx-html-updater`\n   - XLSX: `@xlsx-resource-discovery` → `@xlsx-content-extractor` → `@xlsx-outline-generator` → `@xlsx-office-js-generator`\n3. Main agent receives sub-agent outputs and finalizes\n\n---\n\n### 4. FLIGHTS & OVERWRITE SYSTEM\n\n**Flights** (`flights[]` in registry):\n- Feature flags enabled via `.env`: `OAGENT_FLIGHTS=<flightKey>:true`\n- Runtime overrides of registry config\n- Scoped to specific versions via `applicableVersions`\n- Can override: `version`, `model`, `subagents`, `scripts`, `raiGuidelines`, `overwrites`\n\n**File Overwrites** (`overwrites[]`):\n- Conditional file replacements applied after artifacts are copied\n- Resolution: `src` is relative to `dist/src/prompts/<version>/overwrites/`, `dst` is relative to `/agent/.claude/`\n- Used by flights like `OfficeAgent.CreateAgent.Researcher` to swap entire skill definitions\n- Example: `{ src: 'researcher/researcher.md', dst: 'agents/researcher.md' }`\n\n**Flight Examples in create-agent**:\n- `OfficeAgent.EnableCreateAgent@1.1.0` - Switch to v1.1.0\n- `OfficeAgent.CreateAgent.Researcher` - Add researcher sub-agent + swap prompts\n- `OfficeAgent.CreateAgent.AutoThemeGeneration` - Auto theme for PPTX\n- `OfficeAgent.CreateAgent.NewDesign` - Premium design system (29 themes, 60+ CSS components)\n- `OfficeAgent.CreateAgent.DocxAutoMode` - Model-first DOCX without clarifications\n- `OfficeAgent.XlsxVisualDescription` - Visual description support for Excel\n\n---\n\n### 5. CORE MODULE EXPORTS\n\n**`@officeagent/core` exports** (`/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/index.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport * from './agent';       // BaseAgent, AgentRegistry, AgentWorkspaceManager, config types\nexport * from './logging';     // logInfo, logWarn, logError, logDebug\nexport * from './websocket';   // WebSocketRouter, OfficeAgentSettingsManager\nexport * from './utils';       // Utilities\n```\n\n**Key Types**:\n- `AgentRegistryConfig` - Main registry type\n- `AgentVersionConfig` - Per-version configuration\n- `ResolvedAgentConfig` - Final config after flight/filter resolution\n- `FlightOverride`, `FilterRule` - Dynamic config overrides\n- `BaseAgent` - Abstract base class for all agents\n- `SessionContext` - Runtime context (requestId, sessionId, wsRouter, settingsManager, mcpServers)\n- `TurnContext` - Per-turn data (workspaceManager, requestContext)\n\n**Agent File Types**:\n- `AgentVersionConfig` fields: `version`, `model`, `maxThinkingTokens`, `maxTurns`, `systemPrompt`, `raiGuidelines`, `allowedTools`, `disallowedTools`, `skills`, `subagents`, `scripts`, `intentDetectionDir`, `overwrites`, `harness`\n\n---\n\n### 6. API MODULE: Handler Registry for Internal Messages\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/`\n\n**Purpose**: Central registry for internal message handlers (non-WebSocket, internal-only)\n\n**Key Components**:\n- `HandlerRegistry` - Routes internal messages to handlers\n- `InternalMessageHandler<TRequest, TResponse>` - Handler interface with `handle()`, `validate()`, `handleStream()`, `timeout`\n- `StreamingContext` - For SSE streaming responses (`writeChunk`, `writeEvent`, `end`)\n\n**Built-in Handlers** (in `internal/handlers/`):\n- `WebSearchHandler` - Web search execution\n- `EnterpriseSearchHandler` - Enterprise/Copilot search\n- `EnterpriseFetchHandler` - Fetch grounded content\n- `UserContextHandler` - Get user/account context\n- `ImageSearchHandler` - Image discovery\n- `CitationInjectionHandler` - Process citations in documents\n- `ExcelParseHandler` - Parse Excel files\n- `PptxSlideCountHandler` - Get PowerPoint metadata\n\n**Agent Registration** (`agents.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport function registerAgents(): void {\n    const agents: BaseAgent[] = [\n        new CreateAgent(),           // id: 'create-agent' (Claude)\n        new GPTCreateAgent(),        // id: 'create-agent-gpt'\n        new DWAccountantAgent(),\n        new DWParalegalAgent(),\n        new DWMarketerAgent(),\n        new WorkspaceAgent(),\n        new ODSPAgent(),\n        new PptCreationAgent(),\n        new PptEditAgent(),\n        new ExcelJsRunnerAgent(),\n        new ExcelAgent(),            // id: 'excel-agent' (Copilot SDK)\n        new PptAgent(),\n        new GroundingAgent(),\n        new OfficeAgent(),           // id: 'office-agent' (Copilot SDK)\n    ];\n    \n    for (const agent of agents) {\n        AgentRegistry.registerAgent(agent);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. ORCHESTRATOR: Multi-Provider Abstraction Layer\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/orchestrator/src/`\n\n**Purpose**: Abstraction over multiple LLM providers (Claude, GhcpOrchestrator for GitHub Copilot SDK)\n\n**Key Exports**:\n- `IOrchestrator` - Provider-agnostic interface\n- `OrchestratorRequest`, `OrchestratorResult` - Standard message types\n- `ClaudeOrchestrator`, `GhcpOrchestrator` - Concrete provider implementations\n- `createOrchestrator()`, `registerProvider()` - Factory pattern\n- `HarnessType` - 'claude' | 'ghcp' | other providers\n\n**Key Types**:\n```typescript\ninterface OrchestratorRequest {\n    model?: string;\n    systemPrompt?: string;\n    messages: OrchestratorMessage[];\n    tools?: OrchestratorToolInput[];\n    maxThinkingTokens?: number;\n}\n\ninterface OrchestratorResult {\n    message: OrchestratorMessage;\n    toolCalls?: OrchestratorToolDecision[];\n    usage?: OrchestratorUsage;\n}\n```\n\n**How Agents Use It**:\n- Agent specifies `harness: 'claude' | 'ghcp'` in registry\n- `CreateAgent` uses `claude` (direct Anthropic SDK)\n- `OfficeAgent` uses `ghcp` (GitHub Copilot SDK / GhcpOrchestrator)\n\n---\n\n### 8. MESSAGE PROTOCOL\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/message-protocol/src/types/`\n\n**Core Types**:\n- `MessageType` - Enum for all message types (ChatRequest, TaskUpdate, etc.)\n- `JsonRpcRequest`, `JsonRpcResponse`, `JsonRpcNotification` - JSON-RPC 2.0 types\n- `JsonRpcMethod` - Method names ('chat_request', 'agent_request', etc.)\n- `InternalErrorCode` - Error code enum\n\n**Agent-Specific Types**:\n- `CreateAgentRequest`, `CreateAgentResponse` - Document creation\n- `WorkspaceAgentRequest` - Workspace artifact generation\n- `GroundingAgentTypes` - Grounding/search types\n\n**Grounding Types**:\n- `IEnterpriseSearchRequest`, `IEnterpriseSearchResult`\n- `ImageSearchRequest`, `ImageSearchResult`\n- `SydneyMessage` (re-exported from `@augloop-types/sydney`)\n- `CitationResult` - Clickable citations in documents\n\n**Sensitivity Label Types** - For data classification\n\n**Excel/PowerPoint App Types** - App-specific message structures\n\n---\n\n### 9. DOCUMENTATION ARCHITECTURE\n\n**Key Docs** in `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/docs/`:\n- `BEST_PRACTICES.md` - Code org, package naming, logging, testing, build pipeline\n- `WORKSPACE_AGENT_DESIGN.md` - Two-phase sub-agent architecture (Planner → Generator)\n- `AgentRequestMessage-WebSocket-Flow.md` - Message flow diagrams\n- `EXCEL_HEADLESS.md` - Headless Excel service for cloud xlsx creation\n- `IMAGE_SEARCH_INTEGRATION.md` - Image search grounding flow\n- `AZURE_OPENAI_DESIGN.md` - OpenAI harness integration\n- `PYTHON_TESTING.md` - pytest framework and coverage\n\n**Agent-Specific Docs**:\n- `agents/create-agent/CLAUDE.md` - Create Agent deep dive (systems, hooks, excel-specific notes)\n- `agents/office-agent/CLAUDE.md` - Office Agent (GhcpOrchestrator variant)\n- `agents/ppt-creation-agent/CLAUDE.md` - Minimal PPT Creation Agent\n\n---\n\n### 10. KEY ARCHITECTURE PATTERNS\n\n**Pattern 1: Registry-Driven Configuration**\n- All agent capabilities defined in registry\n- Resolves at runtime with flights applied\n- Decouples agent code from prompt versioning\n\n**Pattern 2: Versioned Prompt Isolation**\n- Each version has complete `/prompts/<version>/` directory\n- Skills, subagents, scripts per-version\n- Flights can selectively overwrite individual files\n\n**Pattern 3: Sub-Agent Pipeline Architecture**\n- Main agent spawns independent sub-agents for scoped tasks\n- Sub-agents can run in parallel or sequence\n- Main agent aggregates results\n- Each sub-agent has own system prompt + tools + model config\n\n**Pattern 4: Hook-Based Extension**\n- Agents register hook providers (agent-specific implementations)\n- Hooks intercept tool use, system prompt building, post-execution\n- `BaseHooksProvider`, `WordHooksProvider`, `ExcelHooksProvider`, `PowerPointHooksProvider`\n\n**Pattern 5: Multi-Harness Abstraction**\n- Agents specify harness ('claude', 'ghcp', etc.) in registry\n- Orchestrator abstracts provider differences\n- Allows seamless switching between Anthropic and GitHub Copilot SDKs\n\n**Pattern 6: Flights for Feature Gating**\n- Feature flags in registry\n- Runtime resolution via `settingsManager.getBooleanSetting()`\n- Can override version, model, subagents, entire prompts\n- Enables A/B testing, gradual rollouts\n\n**Pattern 7: Handler Registry for Internal APIs**\n- Internal message handlers registered separately from main agent\n- Supports streaming (SSE) and non-streaming responses\n- Central routing for enterprise search, image search, excel parse, etc.\n\n---\n\n### Files Referenced\n\n**Core**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/agent/base-agent.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/agent/agent-registry.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/agent/types.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/index.ts`\n\n**Agents**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/registry.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/CLAUDE.md`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/ppt-creation-agent/src/registry.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/office-agent/src/registry.ts`\n\n**Prompts**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.1.0/skills/docx/SKILL.md`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.1.0/subagents/docx-outline-generator.md`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.1.0/system-prompt.md`\n\n**API & Handlers**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/index.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/agents.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/internal/registry/handler-registry.ts`\n\n**Orchestration**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/orchestrator/src/index.ts`\n\n**Protocol**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/message-protocol/src/index.ts`\n\n**Documentation**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/docs/BEST_PRACTICES.md`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/docs/WORKSPACE_AGENT_DESIGN.md`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adf15baed02228452 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 66782\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 156070</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"059c34c4-4758-4e2f-87ba-9357713e7c91","uuid":"df5719ec-7345-402a-9a9c-f46c7dc73902","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the OfficeAgent repo at C:/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent. I need to understand the agent architecture patterns. Do a \"very thorough\" exploration:\n\n1. Read `agents/create-agent/src/registry.ts` - this is the most complex agent\n2. Read `agents/create-agent/CLAUDE.md` \n3. Read `agents/ppt-creation-agent/src/registry.ts` - simpler agent for comparison\n4. Read `agents/office-agent/src/registry.ts` if it exists\n5. Read `modules/core/src/index.ts` or list its exports\n6. Read `modules/api/src/index.ts` or list its exports\n7. Read `modules/orchestrator/src/index.ts` if it exists\n8. List the structure of `agents/create-agent/src/prompts/` (2 levels deep)\n9. Read `modules/message-protocol/src/index.ts` to understand message types\n10. Check `docs/` directory - list all .md files and read any architecture-related ones\n\nReturn a structured summary of:\n- How agents are structured (registry pattern, prompt organization, skills vs subagents)\n- Core module exports and purpose\n- API module purpose and handler registry\n- Message protocol types\n- Orchestrator role (if exists)\n- Key documentation files found","agentId":"adf15baed02228452","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Structured Summary: OfficeAgent Architecture Patterns\n\n### 1. HOW AGENTS ARE STRUCTURED: Registry Pattern\n\n**Core Pattern**: Every agent exports an `AgentRegistryConfig` from `src/registry.ts` that defines:\n- **Metadata**: `id`, `name`, `packageName`, `description`\n- **Versions**: Array of `AgentVersionConfig` objects with model, tools, skills, subagents, scripts\n- **Flights**: Feature flags that override config at runtime\n- **Filters**: Rules to conditionally remove capabilities based on context\n\n**Two Types of Agents**:\n\n1. **Simple Agents** (e.g., `ppt-creation-agent`, `office-agent`):\n   - Minimal registry with only metadata\n   - Single version or no versions\n   - No skills/subagents/flights\n   - No prompt structure needed\n   - Example: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/ppt-creation-agent/src/registry.ts` (14 lines)\n\n2. **Complex Agents** (e.g., `create-agent`):\n   - Multiple versioned configurations (1.0.0, 1.1.0, 1.2.0, 1.2.1)\n   - Per-version: model, tools, skills, subagents, scripts, intent-detection prompts\n   - Multiple flights for feature experimentation\n   - Full prompt directory structure: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/<version>/`\n\n**Registry File Structure** (`AgentRegistryConfig`):\n```typescript\n{\n  id: 'create-agent',\n  name: 'Create Agent',\n  packageName: '@officeagent/create-agent',\n  description: '...',\n  defaultVersion: '1.0.0',\n  versions: [\n    {\n      version: '1.0.0',\n      model: 'claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929',\n      maxThinkingTokens: 1024,\n      maxTurns: 2000,\n      systemPrompt: './system-prompt.md',\n      raiGuidelines: './rai.md',\n      allowedTools: [...],\n      skills: ['docx', 'pptx', 'xlsx', 'image-search'],\n      subagents: ['docx-page-subagent', ...],\n      scripts: ['send-clarification-config.js', ...],\n      intentDetectionDir: ['CLARIFICATION.md', ...]\n    }\n  ],\n  flights: [\n    {\n      flightKey: 'OfficeAgent.EnableCreateAgent@1.1.0',\n      config: { version: '1.1.0' },\n      applicableVersions?: ['1.1.0']\n    }\n  ],\n  filters: []\n}\n```\n\n**Agent Base Class Hierarchy**:\n- All agents extend `BaseAgent` from `@officeagent/core`\n- Constructor receives registry\n- `initialize(context: SessionContext)` resolves config with flights and filters applied\n- `ConfigResolver.resolve()` builds final `ResolvedAgentConfig` after applying:\n  1. Version selection\n  2. Flight overrides (if enabled via `settingsManager`)\n  3. Filter rules (remove skills/subagents/tools based on context)\n\n**Example Agent Classes**:\n- `CreateAgent` extends `BaseAgent` (180+ lines of orchestration)\n- Registers hook providers (`BaseHooksProvider`, `WordHooksProvider`, `ExcelHooksProvider`, `PowerPointHooksProvider`)\n- Manages workspace, chat history, state\n\n---\n\n### 2. PROMPT ORGANIZATION: Versioned Directory Structure\n\nLocated at: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/<version>/`\n\n**Create Agent v1.1.0 Structure**:\n```\nprompts/1.1.0/\n├── system-prompt.md           # EJS-templated main prompt\n├── rai.md / rai_v1.md         # Responsible AI guidelines\n├── agent-capabilities/        # Per-document-type descriptions\n│   ├── word.md\n│   ├── excel.md\n│   └── powerpoint.md\n├── intent-detection/          # Request interceptor prompts\n│   ├── CLARIFICATION.md\n│   ├── CHAT_REPLY.md\n│   ├── INTENT_DETECTION_PROMPT.md\n│   ├── LANGUAGE_DETECTION_PROMPT.md\n│   └── PPT_CLARIFICATION.md\n├── skills/                    # 7 skills\n│   ├── docx/SKILL.md\n│   ├── pptx/SKILL.md\n│   ├── xlsx/SKILL.md\n│   ├── image-search/SKILL.md\n│   ├── pdf/SKILL.md\n│   ├── web-search/SKILL.md\n│   └── web-fetch/SKILL.md\n├── subagents/                 # 10 sub-agents\n│   ├── docx-outline-generator.md\n│   ├── docx-section-generator.md\n│   ├── pptx-outline-generator.md\n│   ├── pptx-html-creator-validator.md\n│   ├── pptx-html-updater.md\n│   ├── pptx-theme-extractor.md\n│   ├── xlsx-resource-discovery.md\n│   ├── xlsx-content-extractor.md\n│   ├── xlsx-outline-generator.md\n│   └── xlsx-office-js-generator.md\n├── scripts/                   # Runtime JS/Python scripts (30+ files)\n│   ├── web-search.js\n│   ├── enterprise-search.js\n│   ├── image-search.js\n│   ├── fetch-user-context.js\n│   └── ... (27 more)\n└── overwrites/                # Flight-conditional file replacements\n    ├── docx/\n    ├── pptx/\n    ├── xlsx/\n    └── researcher/\n```\n\n**Skill Definition** (`SKILL.md`):\n- YAML frontmatter: `name`, `description`\n- Markdown instructions with examples\n- Nested subdirectories for conversion pipelines, validation rules, themes\n- Example from docx/SKILL.md: 5-phase workflow (Requirements → Outline → Sections → DOCX → Delivery)\n\n**Sub-Agent Definition** (`.md` in `subagents/`):\n- YAML frontmatter: `name`, `description`, `tools`\n- Role description and constraints\n- Available scripts (scripts are defined once in `scripts/` and referenced)\n- Instruction sequence for the sub-agent's task\n\n---\n\n### 3. SKILLS VS SUB-AGENTS\n\n**Skills** (defined in `skills/<name>/SKILL.md`):\n- Set of instructions + scripts the main agent follows directly\n- Main agent orchestrates execution sequentially\n- Shared by all instances of the agent in the same turn\n- Example: `docx` skill guides main agent through document creation workflow\n- **When to use**: General capability the main agent needs (search, clarification, image processing)\n\n**Sub-Agents** (defined in `subagents/<name>.md`):\n- Independent Claude instances with isolated system prompt\n- Spawn separately via Task tool: `@docx-outline-generator`, `@pptx-html-creator-validator`\n- Can run in parallel\n- Own context window, tools, and model configuration\n- Example flow: `docx-outline-generator` → parallel `docx-section-generator` instances → main agent finalizes\n- **When to use**: Well-scoped pipeline step needing isolation, parallel execution, or focused context\n\n**Create Agent Pipeline Example (v1.1.0)**:\n1. Main agent determines document type and theme\n2. Spawns sub-agents in sequence/parallel:\n   - DOCX: `@docx-outline-generator` (research) → multiple `@docx-section-generator` (write sections in parallel)\n   - PPTX: `@pptx-outline-generator` → `@pptx-html-creator-validator` → `@pptx-html-updater`\n   - XLSX: `@xlsx-resource-discovery` → `@xlsx-content-extractor` → `@xlsx-outline-generator` → `@xlsx-office-js-generator`\n3. Main agent receives sub-agent outputs and finalizes\n\n---\n\n### 4. FLIGHTS & OVERWRITE SYSTEM\n\n**Flights** (`flights[]` in registry):\n- Feature flags enabled via `.env`: `OAGENT_FLIGHTS=<flightKey>:true`\n- Runtime overrides of registry config\n- Scoped to specific versions via `applicableVersions`\n- Can override: `version`, `model`, `subagents`, `scripts`, `raiGuidelines`, `overwrites`\n\n**File Overwrites** (`overwrites[]`):\n- Conditional file replacements applied after artifacts are copied\n- Resolution: `src` is relative to `dist/src/prompts/<version>/overwrites/`, `dst` is relative to `/agent/.claude/`\n- Used by flights like `OfficeAgent.CreateAgent.Researcher` to swap entire skill definitions\n- Example: `{ src: 'researcher/researcher.md', dst: 'agents/researcher.md' }`\n\n**Flight Examples in create-agent**:\n- `OfficeAgent.EnableCreateAgent@1.1.0` - Switch to v1.1.0\n- `OfficeAgent.CreateAgent.Researcher` - Add researcher sub-agent + swap prompts\n- `OfficeAgent.CreateAgent.AutoThemeGeneration` - Auto theme for PPTX\n- `OfficeAgent.CreateAgent.NewDesign` - Premium design system (29 themes, 60+ CSS components)\n- `OfficeAgent.CreateAgent.DocxAutoMode` - Model-first DOCX without clarifications\n- `OfficeAgent.XlsxVisualDescription` - Visual description support for Excel\n\n---\n\n### 5. CORE MODULE EXPORTS\n\n**`@officeagent/core` exports** (`/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/index.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport * from './agent';       // BaseAgent, AgentRegistry, AgentWorkspaceManager, config types\nexport * from './logging';     // logInfo, logWarn, logError, logDebug\nexport * from './websocket';   // WebSocketRouter, OfficeAgentSettingsManager\nexport * from './utils';       // Utilities\n```\n\n**Key Types**:\n- `AgentRegistryConfig` - Main registry type\n- `AgentVersionConfig` - Per-version configuration\n- `ResolvedAgentConfig` - Final config after flight/filter resolution\n- `FlightOverride`, `FilterRule` - Dynamic config overrides\n- `BaseAgent` - Abstract base class for all agents\n- `SessionContext` - Runtime context (requestId, sessionId, wsRouter, settingsManager, mcpServers)\n- `TurnContext` - Per-turn data (workspaceManager, requestContext)\n\n**Agent File Types**:\n- `AgentVersionConfig` fields: `version`, `model`, `maxThinkingTokens`, `maxTurns`, `systemPrompt`, `raiGuidelines`, `allowedTools`, `disallowedTools`, `skills`, `subagents`, `scripts`, `intentDetectionDir`, `overwrites`, `harness`\n\n---\n\n### 6. API MODULE: Handler Registry for Internal Messages\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/`\n\n**Purpose**: Central registry for internal message handlers (non-WebSocket, internal-only)\n\n**Key Components**:\n- `HandlerRegistry` - Routes internal messages to handlers\n- `InternalMessageHandler<TRequest, TResponse>` - Handler interface with `handle()`, `validate()`, `handleStream()`, `timeout`\n- `StreamingContext` - For SSE streaming responses (`writeChunk`, `writeEvent`, `end`)\n\n**Built-in Handlers** (in `internal/handlers/`):\n- `WebSearchHandler` - Web search execution\n- `EnterpriseSearchHandler` - Enterprise/Copilot search\n- `EnterpriseFetchHandler` - Fetch grounded content\n- `UserContextHandler` - Get user/account context\n- `ImageSearchHandler` - Image discovery\n- `CitationInjectionHandler` - Process citations in documents\n- `ExcelParseHandler` - Parse Excel files\n- `PptxSlideCountHandler` - Get PowerPoint metadata\n\n**Agent Registration** (`agents.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport function registerAgents(): void {\n    const agents: BaseAgent[] = [\n        new CreateAgent(),           // id: 'create-agent' (Claude)\n        new GPTCreateAgent(),        // id: 'create-agent-gpt'\n        new DWAccountantAgent(),\n        new DWParalegalAgent(),\n        new DWMarketerAgent(),\n        new WorkspaceAgent(),\n        new ODSPAgent(),\n        new PptCreationAgent(),\n        new PptEditAgent(),\n        new ExcelJsRunnerAgent(),\n        new ExcelAgent(),            // id: 'excel-agent' (Copilot SDK)\n        new PptAgent(),\n        new GroundingAgent(),\n        new OfficeAgent(),           // id: 'office-agent' (Copilot SDK)\n    ];\n    \n    for (const agent of agents) {\n        AgentRegistry.registerAgent(agent);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. ORCHESTRATOR: Multi-Provider Abstraction Layer\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/orchestrator/src/`\n\n**Purpose**: Abstraction over multiple LLM providers (Claude, GhcpOrchestrator for GitHub Copilot SDK)\n\n**Key Exports**:\n- `IOrchestrator` - Provider-agnostic interface\n- `OrchestratorRequest`, `OrchestratorResult` - Standard message types\n- `ClaudeOrchestrator`, `GhcpOrchestrator` - Concrete provider implementations\n- `createOrchestrator()`, `registerProvider()` - Factory pattern\n- `HarnessType` - 'claude' | 'ghcp' | other providers\n\n**Key Types**:\n```typescript\ninterface OrchestratorRequest {\n    model?: string;\n    systemPrompt?: string;\n    messages: OrchestratorMessage[];\n    tools?: OrchestratorToolInput[];\n    maxThinkingTokens?: number;\n}\n\ninterface OrchestratorResult {\n    message: OrchestratorMessage;\n    toolCalls?: OrchestratorToolDecision[];\n    usage?: OrchestratorUsage;\n}\n```\n\n**How Agents Use It**:\n- Agent specifies `harness: 'claude' | 'ghcp'` in registry\n- `CreateAgent` uses `claude` (direct Anthropic SDK)\n- `OfficeAgent` uses `ghcp` (GitHub Copilot SDK / GhcpOrchestrator)\n\n---\n\n### 8. MESSAGE PROTOCOL\n\n**Location**: `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/message-protocol/src/types/`\n\n**Core Types**:\n- `MessageType` - Enum for all message types (ChatRequest, TaskUpdate, etc.)\n- `JsonRpcRequest`, `JsonRpcResponse`, `JsonRpcNotification` - JSON-RPC 2.0 types\n- `JsonRpcMethod` - Method names ('chat_request', 'agent_request', etc.)\n- `InternalErrorCode` - Error code enum\n\n**Agent-Specific Types**:\n- `CreateAgentRequest`, `CreateAgentResponse` - Document creation\n- `WorkspaceAgentRequest` - Workspace artifact generation\n- `GroundingAgentTypes` - Grounding/search types\n\n**Grounding Types**:\n- `IEnterpriseSearchRequest`, `IEnterpriseSearchResult`\n- `ImageSearchRequest`, `ImageSearchResult`\n- `SydneyMessage` (re-exported from `@augloop-types/sydney`)\n- `CitationResult` - Clickable citations in documents\n\n**Sensitivity Label Types** - For data classification\n\n**Excel/PowerPoint App Types** - App-specific message structures\n\n---\n\n### 9. DOCUMENTATION ARCHITECTURE\n\n**Key Docs** in `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/docs/`:\n- `BEST_PRACTICES.md` - Code org, package naming, logging, testing, build pipeline\n- `WORKSPACE_AGENT_DESIGN.md` - Two-phase sub-agent architecture (Planner → Generator)\n- `AgentRequestMessage-WebSocket-Flow.md` - Message flow diagrams\n- `EXCEL_HEADLESS.md` - Headless Excel service for cloud xlsx creation\n- `IMAGE_SEARCH_INTEGRATION.md` - Image search grounding flow\n- `AZURE_OPENAI_DESIGN.md` - OpenAI harness integration\n- `PYTHON_TESTING.md` - pytest framework and coverage\n\n**Agent-Specific Docs**:\n- `agents/create-agent/CLAUDE.md` - Create Agent deep dive (systems, hooks, excel-specific notes)\n- `agents/office-agent/CLAUDE.md` - Office Agent (GhcpOrchestrator variant)\n- `agents/ppt-creation-agent/CLAUDE.md` - Minimal PPT Creation Agent\n\n---\n\n### 10. KEY ARCHITECTURE PATTERNS\n\n**Pattern 1: Registry-Driven Configuration**\n- All agent capabilities defined in registry\n- Resolves at runtime with flights applied\n- Decouples agent code from prompt versioning\n\n**Pattern 2: Versioned Prompt Isolation**\n- Each version has complete `/prompts/<version>/` directory\n- Skills, subagents, scripts per-version\n- Flights can selectively overwrite individual files\n\n**Pattern 3: Sub-Agent Pipeline Architecture**\n- Main agent spawns independent sub-agents for scoped tasks\n- Sub-agents can run in parallel or sequence\n- Main agent aggregates results\n- Each sub-agent has own system prompt + tools + model config\n\n**Pattern 4: Hook-Based Extension**\n- Agents register hook providers (agent-specific implementations)\n- Hooks intercept tool use, system prompt building, post-execution\n- `BaseHooksProvider`, `WordHooksProvider`, `ExcelHooksProvider`, `PowerPointHooksProvider`\n\n**Pattern 5: Multi-Harness Abstraction**\n- Agents specify harness ('claude', 'ghcp', etc.) in registry\n- Orchestrator abstracts provider differences\n- Allows seamless switching between Anthropic and GitHub Copilot SDKs\n\n**Pattern 6: Flights for Feature Gating**\n- Feature flags in registry\n- Runtime resolution via `settingsManager.getBooleanSetting()`\n- Can override version, model, subagents, entire prompts\n- Enables A/B testing, gradual rollouts\n\n**Pattern 7: Handler Registry for Internal APIs**\n- Internal message handlers registered separately from main agent\n- Supports streaming (SSE) and non-streaming responses\n- Central routing for enterprise search, image search, excel parse, etc.\n\n---\n\n### Files Referenced\n\n**Core**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/agent/base-agent.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/agent/agent-registry.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/agent/types.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/core/src/index.ts`\n\n**Agents**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/registry.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/CLAUDE.md`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/create-agent.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/ppt-creation-agent/src/registry.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/office-agent/src/registry.ts`\n\n**Prompts**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.1.0/skills/docx/SKILL.md`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.1.0/subagents/docx-outline-generator.md`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/agents/create-agent/src/prompts/1.1.0/system-prompt.md`\n\n**API & Handlers**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/index.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/agents.ts`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/api/src/internal/registry/handler-registry.ts`\n\n**Orchestration**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/orchestrator/src/index.ts`\n\n**Protocol**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/modules/message-protocol/src/index.ts`\n\n**Documentation**:\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/docs/BEST_PRACTICES.md`\n- `/c/Users/yemishin/OfficeAgent/docs/WORKSPACE_AGENT_DESIGN.md`"}],"totalDurationMs":156070,"totalTokens":66782,"totalToolUseCount":32,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1061,"c