{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HnrgkeS7ScqR74nxumFnuk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FGnud8tjDM8iGzAPeeDDtp","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\yemishin\\.squad\\notes\\inbox\\ripley-2026-03-14.md","content":"# Ripley — OfficeAgent Deep Exploration Findings\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-14 (updated)\n**Task:** Full codebase architecture exploration of OfficeAgent monorepo\n\n## Area Explored\n\nComplete OfficeAgent monorepo: agents/ (14 agents), modules/ (17 packages), .devtools/, eval/, docs/, docker/, build system, Claude skills/commands.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Overview\nOfficeAgent is an AI-powered document generation platform running in Docker containers. It uses Claude SDK and Azure OpenAI (via GitHub Copilot SDK) to create DOCX, PPTX, XLSX, and PDF files. The system is a Yarn 4.10.3 monorepo with lage task orchestration, TypeScript 5.9, Node 24+, and a Python evaluation framework.\n\n### Message Flow\n```\nClient (WebSocket on :6010)\n  → API Module (app.ts) → WebSocket/HTTP routing\n    → Core (WebSocketManager/Router)\n      → Handler Registry (typed message dispatch)\n        → Orchestrator (Claude SDK or GHCP)\n          → Grounding Pipeline (enterprise search, image, web)\n            → Agent execution (skills, sub-agents, hooks)\n              → Chain-of-Thought tracking\n                → Response streamed back to client\n```\n\n### Three-Tier Agent Architecture\n1. **Full Claude SDK agents** (create-agent): Multi-version, sub-agents, 20+ flights, request interceptors, hooks by agent type. The most complex — `create-agent.ts` is ~84KB.\n2. **Copilot SDK agents** (office-agent, excel-agent): Simpler, use GhcpOrchestrator, import shared services from create-agent.\n3. **Minimal agents** (ppt-creation-agent): No LLM, direct HTML→PPTX conversion, bare registry.\n\n### Orchestrator Abstraction\n`@officeagent/orchestrator` provides a provider-agnostic `IOrchestrator` interface:\n- `ClaudeOrchestrator` — Claude SDK wrapper\n- `GhcpOrchestrator` — GitHub Copilot SDK wrapper\n- Factory pattern: `createOrchestrator()` selects provider at runtime\n- Common types: `OrchestratorRequest`, `OrchestratorMessage`, `OrchestratorResult`\n\n### Agent Registry — All 14 Registered Agents\n```typescript\n// From modules/api/src/agents.ts\nCreateAgent         // 'create-agent' — Claude SDK, full pipeline\nGPTCreateAgent      // 'create-agent-gpt' — Azure OpenAI variant\nDWAccountantAgent   // DataWorks Accountant\nDWParalegalAgent    // DataWorks Paralegal\nDWMarketerAgent     // DataWorks Marketer\nWorkspaceAgent      // Workspace artifact generation\nODSPAgent           // ODSP integration\nPptCreationAgent    // Direct HTML→PPTX (no LLM)\nPptEditAgent        // PPT editing\nExcelJsRunnerAgent  // Excel JS execution\nExcelAgent          // Excel via Copilot SDK\nPptAgent            // PPT via Copilot SDK\nGroundingAgent      // Enterprise search/grounding\nOfficeAgent         // Office via Copilot SDK (GhcpOrchestrator)\n```\n\n## Patterns\n\n### 1. Registry-First Agent Design\nEvery agent exports `agentRegistry: AgentRegistryConfig` from `src/registry.ts`:\n- Identity: id, name, packageName, description\n- Versions array with model, tools, skills, subagents, scripts\n- Flights (static feature flags) and Filters (dynamic runtime rules)\n- Default version selection + flight-based version overrides\n\n### 2. Versioned Prompt Organization\n```\nsrc/prompts/<version>/\n├── system-prompt.md (EJS templates with <%- variable %>)\n├── rai.md\n├── skills/<name>/SKILL.md (YAML frontmatter + instructions)\n├── subagents/<name>.md (YAML frontmatter: name, description, tools)\n├── scripts/ (JS/Python runtime scripts, 30+ in create-agent v1.1.0)\n├── agent-capabilities/ (per-doc-type: word.md, excel.md, powerpoint.md)\n├── intent-detection/ (CLARIFICATION.md, CHAT_REPLY.md, etc.)\n└── overwrites/ (flight-conditional file replacements)\n```\n\n### 3. Skills vs Sub-Agents\n- **Skills**: Instructions + scripts the agent follows directly (shared context window)\n- **Sub-agents**: Isolated Claude instances with own system prompt (parallel, focused)\n- Pattern: well-scoped pipeline steps → sub-agent; general capabilities → skill\n- **Create-agent sub-agent pipeline example**:\n  - DOCX: `@docx-outline-generator` → parallel `@docx-section-generator` instances\n  - PPTX: `@pptx-outline-generator` → `@pptx-html-creator-validator` → `@pptx-html-updater`\n  - XLSX: `@xlsx-resource-discovery` → `@xlsx-content-extractor` → `@xlsx-outline-generator` → `@xlsx-office-js-generator`\n\n### 4. Hook System\n- `HookRegistry` with per-agent-type providers (Base, Word, Excel, PowerPoint)\n- Hooks: PreToolUse, PostToolUse, SessionStart, SessionEnd, startTurn\n- Used for performance tracking, CoT streaming, output validation\n\n### 5. Flight System (Feature Gating)\n- Feature flags in registry, enabled via `OAGENT_FLIGHTS=<key>:true`\n- Can override: version, model, subagents, scripts, raiGuidelines, entire prompt files\n- Flights scoped to specific versions via `applicableVersions`\n- Flight overwrite mechanism: `{ src: 'overwrites/file.md', dst: 'skills/path/file.md' }`\n- Example flights in create-agent: `@1.1.0`, `@1.2.0`, Researcher, AutoThemeGeneration, NewDesign, DocxAutoMode\n\n### 6. Grounding Pipeline (4-Stage)\n`@officeagent/grounding` implements: Preprocessor → Retriever → Postprocessor → Storage\n- Entity-specific extractors: Email, File, Chat, Meeting, People, Calendar, Transcript\n- A2A (Agent-to-Agent) HTTP communication pattern\n\n### 7. Internal Handler Registry\nAPI module provides typed handlers for internal (non-WebSocket) operations:\n- WebSearchHandler, EnterpriseSearchHandler, EnterpriseFetchHandler\n- UserContextHandler, ImageSearchHandler, CitationInjectionHandler\n- ExcelParseHandler, PptxSlideCountHandler\n- Supports both streaming (SSE) and synchronous responses\n\n### 8. Build & Runtime\n- PowerShell required for yarn/oagent/gulp commands on Windows\n- Docker multi-stage build: poppler + LibreOffice 26.2 + Node 24 + OfficePy base image\n- Ports: 6010 (external API), 6011 (internal), 6020 (debug), 7010 (grounding)\n- Hot reload: `yarn reload` copies dist to running container\n- Health check: `curl http://localhost:6010/health`\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Module Dependency Graph (key paths)\n- **All agents** → `@officeagent/core` (BaseAgent, logging, WebSocket)\n- **All agents** → `@officeagent/message-protocol` (message types, JSON-RPC 2.0)\n- **create-agent** → `@officeagent/grounding`, `@officeagent/rai`, `@officeagent/chain-of-thought`, `@officeagent/excel-headless`\n- **office-agent** → `@officeagent/create-agent` (imports shared services, hooks)\n- **API** → `@officeagent/core`, `@officeagent/message-protocol`, `@officeagent/mcp-proxy`\n- **orchestrator** → no internal deps (provider-agnostic abstraction)\n\n### External Dependencies\n- `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` 0.2.39\n- Express + ws (HTTP/WebSocket)\n- `@augloop-tools/*` (token server, test client)\n- Playwright 1.57.0 (browser automation)\n- docx, pptxgenjs, sharp (document generation)\n- Python: pytest, flask, msal, playwright (eval framework)\n\n## Eval Framework\n\n- Python-based, pytest, 6+ evaluator types: excel, pairwise, societas, content, rule_based, intent\n- CLI: `oagent eval <alias>` for named test suites\n- Configs in `eval/configs/`, datasets in `eval/datasets/`\n- Output structure: `eval/outputs/<run>/` with docs, logs, and eval results\n- Default eval model: `dev-gpt-5-reasoning`\n\n## Claude Skills & Commands (in .claude/)\n\n**Skills**: analyze-pr, office-agent-failure-analysis, prompt-lint, ocv-triage, wxp-agent-testing\n**Commands**: analyze-ocv, commit, eval-pipeline, generate-doc, word-eval\n\n## Gaps\n\n1. **CLAUDE.md coverage**: Missing for dw-marketer-agent, grounding-agent, excel-js-runner-agent, ppt-agent, workspace-agent, excel-agent.\n2. **README.md stale**: Lists 7 agents but there are 14+ in agents/.\n3. **Test coverage visibility**: Only in CI (TF_BUILD=true), no local coverage command.\n4. **No integration test suite**: E2E tests exist in `.devtools/e2e-tests/` but no documented way to run a quick smoke test without Docker.\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **For new agent work**: Start from `agents/create-agent/src/registry.ts` as the canonical reference. Read the agent's CLAUDE.md if present.\n2. **For prompt changes**: Use the flight-based overwrite system rather than mutating base version files. Enables safe A/B testing.\n3. **For shared module changes**: Run `yarn build` (not just compile) to catch Docker packaging issues early.\n4. **For exploration tasks**: `oagent gen \"prompt\" --open` is the fastest feedback loop.\n5. **For eval work**: Activate the Python venv first (`.\\venv\\Scripts\\Activate.ps1`), then use `oagent eval alias` to discover available test suites.\n\n## Key File Locations\n\n| What | Where |\n|------|-------|\n| Agent pattern reference | `agents/create-agent/src/registry.ts` |\n| Agent registration | `modules/api/src/agents.ts` |\n| API entry point | `modules/api/src/app.ts` |\n| Base agent class | `modules/core/src/agent/base-agent.ts` |\n| Config types | `modules/core/src/agent/types.ts` |\n| Message types | `modules/message-protocol/src/types/` |\n| Orchestrator interface | `modules/orchestrator/src/types.ts` |\n| Grounding pipeline | `modules/grounding/src/orchestrator.ts` |\n| Handler registry | `modules/api/src/internal/registry/handler-registry.ts` |\n| Best practices | `docs/BEST_PRACTICES.md` |\n| WebSocket flow doc | `docs/AgentRequestMessage-WebSocket-Flow.md` |\n| Workspace agent design | `docs/WORKSPACE_AGENT_DESIGN.md` |\n| CLI source | `.devtools/cli/` |\n| Eval framework | `eval/` |\n| Docker config | `docker/Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml` |\n| Build config | `lage.config.js`, `gulpfile.mjs` |\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2315,"cache_read_input_tokens":52996,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2315,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"059c34c4-4758-4e2f-87ba-9357713e7c91","uuid":"5c1fe5cc-3dc7-4acb-a8a9-ce717832b035"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FGnud8tjDM8iGzAPeeDDtp","type":"tool_result","content":"The file C:\\Users\\yemishin\\.squad\\notes\\inbox\\ripley-2026-03-14.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"059c34c4-4758-4e2f-87ba-9357713e7c91","uuid":"de85030b-cf83-4651-878f-d1c75082a126","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"C:\\Users\\yemishin\\.squad\\notes\\inbox\\ripley-2026-03-14.md","content":"# Ripley — OfficeAgent Deep Exploration Findings\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-14 (updated)\n**Task:** Full codebase architecture exploration of OfficeAgent monorepo\n\n## Area Explored\n\nComplete OfficeAgent monorepo: agents/ (14 agents), modules/ (17 packages), .devtools/, eval/, docs/, docker/, build system, Claude skills/commands.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Overview\nOfficeAgent is an AI-powered document generation platform running in Docker containers. It uses Claude SDK and Azure OpenAI (via GitHub Copilot SDK) to create DOCX, PPTX, XLSX, and PDF files. The system is a Yarn 4.10.3 monorepo with lage task orchestration, TypeScript 5.9, Node 24+, and a Python evaluation framework.\n\n### Message Flow\n```\nClient (WebSocket on :6010)\n  → API Module (app.ts) → WebSocket/HTTP routing\n    → Core (WebSocketManager/Router)\n      → Handler Registry (typed message dispatch)\n        → Orchestrator (Claude SDK or GHCP)\n          → Grounding Pipeline (enterprise search, image, web)\n            → Agent execution (skills, sub-agents, hooks)\n              → Chain-of-Thought tracking\n                → Response streamed back to client\n```\n\n### Three-Tier Agent Architecture\n1. **Full Claude SDK agents** (create-agent): Multi-version, sub-agents, 20+ flights, request interceptors, hooks by agent type. The most complex — `create-agent.ts` is ~84KB.\n2. **Copilot SDK agents** (office-agent, excel-agent): Simpler, use GhcpOrchestrator, import shared services from create-agent.\n3. **Minimal agents** (ppt-creation-agent): No LLM, direct HTML→PPTX conversion, bare registry.\n\n### Orchestrator Abstraction\n`@officeagent/orchestrator` provides a provider-agnostic `IOrchestrator` interface:\n- `ClaudeOrchestrator` — Claude SDK wrapper\n- `GhcpOrchestrator` — GitHub Copilot SDK wrapper\n- Factory pattern: `createOrchestrator()` selects provider at runtime\n- Common types: `OrchestratorRequest`, `OrchestratorMessage`, `OrchestratorResult`\n\n### Agent Registry — All 14 Registered Agents\n```typescript\n// From modules/api/src/agents.ts\nCreateAgent         // 'create-agent' — Claude SDK, full pipeline\nGPTCreateAgent      // 'create-agent-gpt' — Azure OpenAI variant\nDWAccountantAgent   // DataWorks Accountant\nDWParalegalAgent    // DataWorks Paralegal\nDWMarketerAgent     // DataWorks Marketer\nWorkspaceAgent      // Workspace artifact generation\nODSPAgent           // ODSP integration\nPptCreationAgent    // Direct HTML→PPTX (no LLM)\nPptEditAgent        // PPT editing\nExcelJsRunnerAgent  // Excel JS execution\nExcelAgent          // Excel via Copilot SDK\nPptAgent            // PPT via Copilot SDK\nGroundingAgent      // Enterprise search/grounding\nOfficeAgent         // Office via Copilot SDK (GhcpOrchestrator)\n```\n\n## Patterns\n\n### 1. Registry-First Agent Design\nEvery agent exports `agentRegistry: AgentRegistryConfig` from `src/registry.ts`:\n- Identity: id, name, packageName, description\n- Versions array with model, tools, skills, subagents, scripts\n- Flights (static feature flags) and Filters (dynamic runtime rules)\n- Default version selection + flight-based version overrides\n\n### 2. Versioned Prompt Organization\n```\nsrc/prompts/<version>/\n├── system-prompt.md (EJS templates with <%- variable %>)\n├── rai.md\n├── skills/<name>/SKILL.md (YAML frontmatter + instructions)\n├── subagents/<name>.md (YAML frontmatter: name, description, tools)\n├── scripts/ (JS/Python runtime scripts, 30+ in create-agent v1.1.0)\n├── agent-capabilities/ (per-doc-type: word.md, excel.md, powerpoint.md)\n├── intent-detection/ (CLARIFICATION.md, CHAT_REPLY.md, etc.)\n└── overwrites/ (flight-conditional file replacements)\n```\n\n### 3. Skills vs Sub-Agents\n- **Skills**: Instructions + scripts the agent follows directly (shared context window)\n- **Sub-agents**: Isolated Claude instances with own system prompt (parallel, focused)\n- Pattern: well-scoped pipeline steps → sub-agent; general capabilities → skill\n- **Create-agent sub-agent pipeline example**:\n  - DOCX: `@docx-outline-generator` → parallel `@docx-section-generator` instances\n  - PPTX: `@pptx-outline-generator` → `@pptx-html-creator-validator` → `@pptx-html-updater`\n  - XLSX: `@xlsx-resource-discovery` → `@xlsx-content-extractor` → `@xlsx-outline-generator` → `@xlsx-office-js-generator`\n\n### 4. Hook System\n- `HookRegistry` with per-agent-type providers (Base, Word, Excel, PowerPoint)\n- Hooks: PreToolUse, PostToolUse, SessionStart, SessionEnd, startTurn\n- Used for performance tracking, CoT streaming, output validation\n\n### 5. Flight System (Feature Gating)\n- Feature flags in registry, enabled via `OAGENT_FLIGHTS=<key>:true`\n- Can override: version, model, subagents, scripts, raiGuidelines, entire prompt files\n- Flights scoped to specific versions via `applicableVersions`\n- Flight overwrite mechanism: `{ src: 'overwrites/file.md', dst: 'skills/path/file.md' }`\n- Example flights in create-agent: `@1.1.0`, `@1.2.0`, Researcher, AutoThemeGeneration, NewDesign, DocxAutoMode\n\n### 6. Grounding Pipeline (4-Stage)\n`@officeagent/grounding` implements: Preprocessor → Retriever → Postprocessor → Storage\n- Entity-specific extractors: Email, File, Chat, Meeting, People, Calendar, Transcript\n- A2A (Agent-to-Agent) HTTP communication pattern\n\n### 7. Internal Handler Registry\nAPI module provides typed handlers for internal (non-WebSocket) operations:\n- WebSearchHandler, EnterpriseSearchHandler, EnterpriseFetchHandler\n- UserContextHandler, ImageSearchHandler, CitationInjectionHandler\n- ExcelParseHandler, PptxSlideCountHandler\n- Supports both streaming (SSE) and synchronous responses\n\n### 8. Build & Runtime\n- PowerShell required for yarn/oagent/gulp commands on Windows\n- Docker multi-stage build: poppler + LibreOffice 26.2 + Node 24 + OfficePy base image\n- Ports: 6010 (external API), 6011 (internal), 6020 (debug), 7010 (grounding)\n- Hot reload: `yarn reload` copies dist to running container\n- Health check: `curl http://localhost:6010/health`\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Module Dependency Graph (key paths)\n- **All agents** → `@officeagent/core` (BaseAgent, logging, WebSocket)\n- **All agents** → `@officeagent/message-protocol` (message types, JSON-RPC 2.0)\n- **create-agent** → `@officeagent/grounding`, `@officeagent/rai`, `@officeagent/chain-of-thought`, `@officeagent/excel-headless`\n- **office-agent** → `@officeagent/create-agent` (imports shared services, hooks)\n- **API** → `@officeagent/core`, `@officeagent/message-protocol`, `@officeagent/mcp-proxy`\n- **orchestrator** → no internal deps (provider-agnostic abstraction)\n\n### External Dependencies\n- `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` 0.2.39\n- Express + ws (HTTP/WebSocket)\n- `@augloop-tools/*` (token server, test client)\n- Playwright 1.57.0 (browser automation)\n- docx, pptxgenjs, sharp (document generation)\n- Python: pytest, flask, msal, playwright (eval framework)\n\n## Eval Framework\n\n- Python-based, pytest, 6+ evaluator types: excel, pairwise, societas, content, rule_based, intent\n- CLI: `oagent eval <alias>` for named test suites\n- Configs in `eval/configs/`, datasets in `eval/datasets/`\n- Output structure: `eval/outputs/<run>/` with docs, logs, and eval results\n- Default eval model: `dev-gpt-5-reasoning`\n\n## Claude Skills & Commands (in .claude/)\n\n**Skills**: analyze-pr, office-agent-failure-analysis, prompt-lint, ocv-triage, wxp-agent-testing\n**Commands**: analyze-ocv, commit, eval-pipeline, generate-doc, word-eval\n\n## Gaps\n\n1. **CLAUDE.md coverage**: Missing for dw-marketer-agent, grounding-agent, excel-js-runner-agent, ppt-agent, workspace-agent, excel-agent.\n2. **README.md stale**: Lists 7 agents but there are 14+ in agents/.\n3. **Test coverage visibility**: Only in CI (TF_BUILD=true), no local coverage command.\n4. **No integration test suite**: E2E tests exist in `.devtools/e2e-tests/` but no documented way to run a quick smoke test without Docker.\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **For new agent work**: Start from `agents/create-agent/src/registry.ts` as the canonical reference. Read the agent's CLAUDE.md if present.\n2. **For prompt changes**: Use the flight-based overwrite system rather than mutating base version files. Enables safe A/B testing.\n3. **For shared module changes**: Run `yarn build` (not just compile) to catch Docker packaging issues early.\n4. **For exploration tasks**: `oagent gen \"prompt\" --open` is the fastest feedback loop.\n5. **For eval work**: Activate the Python venv first (`.\\venv\\Scripts\\Activate.ps1`), then use `oagent eval alias` to discover available test suites.\n\n## Key File Locations\n\n| What | Where |\n|------|-------|\n| Agent pattern reference | `agents/create-agent/src/registry.ts` |\n| Agent registration | `modules/api/src/agents.ts` |\n| API entry point | `modules/api/src/app.ts` |\n| Base agent class | `modules/core/src/agent/base-agent.ts` |\n| Config types | `modules/core/src/agent/types.ts` |\n| Message types | `modules/message-protocol/src/types/` |\n| Orchestrator interface | `modules/orchestrator/src/types.ts` |\n| Grounding pipeline | `modules/grounding/src/orchestrator.ts` |\n| Handler registry | `modules/api/src/internal/registry/handler-registry.ts` |\n| Best practices | `docs/BEST_PRACTICES.md` |\n| WebSocket flow doc | `docs/AgentRequestMessage-WebSocket-Flow.md` |\n| Workspace agent design | `docs/WORKSPACE_AGENT_DESIGN.md` |\n| CLI source | `.devtools/cli/` |\n| Eval framework | `eval/` |\n| Docker config | `docker/Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml` |\n| Build config | `lage.config.js`, `gulpfile.mjs` |\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":11,"newStart":1,"newLines":11,"lines":[" # Ripley — OfficeAgent Deep Exploration Findings"," ","-**Date:** 2026-03-14","+**Date:** 2026-03-14 (updated)"," **Task:** Full codebase architecture exploration of OfficeAgent monorepo"," "," ## Area Explored"," ","-Complete OfficeAgent monorepo: agents/, modules/, .devtools/, eval/, docs/, docker/, build system configuration.","+Complete OfficeAgent monorepo: agents/ (14 agents), modules/ (17 packages), .devtools/, eval/, docs/, docker/, build system, Claude skills/commands."," "," ## Architecture"," "]},{"oldStart":37,"oldLines":6,"newStart":37,"newLines":25,"lines":[" - Factory pattern: `createOrchestrator()` selects provider at runtime"," - Common types: `OrchestratorRequest`, `OrchestratorMessage`, `OrchestratorResult`"," ","+### Agent Registry — All 14 Registered Agents","+```typescript","+// From modules/api/src/agents.ts","+CreateAgent         // 'create-agent' — Claude SDK, full pipeline","+GPTCreateAgent      // 'create-agent-gpt' — Azure OpenAI variant","+DWAccountantAgent   // DataWorks Accountant","+DWParalegalAgent    // DataWorks Paralegal","+DWMarketerAgent     // DataWorks Marketer","+WorkspaceAgent      // Workspace artifact generation","+ODSPAgent           // ODSP integration","+PptCreationAgent    // Direct HTML→PPTX (no LLM)","+PptEditAgent        // PPT editing","+ExcelJsRunnerAgent  // Excel JS execution","+ExcelAgent          // Excel via Copilot SDK","+PptAgent            // PPT via Copilot SDK","+GroundingAgent      // Enterprise search/grounding","+OfficeAgent         // Office via Copilot SDK (GhcpOrchestrator)","+```","+"," ## Patterns"," "," ### 1. Registry-First Agent Design"]},{"oldStart":49,"oldLines":42,"newStart":68,"newLines":61,"lines":[" ### 2. Versioned Prompt Organization"," ```"," src/prompts/<version>/","-├── system-prompt.md (EJS templates)","+├── system-pr